title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Cut up boiled eggs on top. Warm celery soup and
broth.
Pour over eggs and chicken.
Mix flour, mayonnaise, margarine
and
milk.
Pour
over
chicken. Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice	enough	apples	to
fill a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (or pan of your chosen size).
Sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture
over apples.
Mix flour, brown sugar and margarine together
and spread over apples in fairly thick coating. Bake at 350° until apples are tender.
Serve warm with whipped cream. Luscious!

title: california sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain, peel and halve lengthwise (or use 1 pound 2 ounce can).
Arrange in shallow dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon salt in small saucepan.
Blend in the orange juice.
Add raisins.
Stir while bringing quickly to boiling. Add remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are well glazed.
Serves 4.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use at least 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture for cup.
Makes 55 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Save some shredded cheese for covering top.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Wash the neck bones; put in a pot with enough water to cover them and let come to a boil.
Turn the heat to low and cook slowly until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove the neck bones from the pot; skim off the fat and strain the liquid.
If necessary, add water to the broth to make 4 cups liquid.
Put the liquid back into the pot and add the peas, onion, garlic salt, thyme and red pepper. Let come to a boil.
Put in the rice.
Stir well and cover. Reduce the heat to low and let cook slowly for about 30 minutes. Meanwhile, pick the meat off the neck bones.
Add it to the peas and rice for a one-dish meal.
Serves 8.

title: meatless noodle casserole
directions: Mix together cooked and drained noodles and oleo.
Beat eggs well; add sugar, sour cream, pineapple and cottage cheese; beat slowly.
Add these ingredients to noodles.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle topping over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for cheese and Ritz crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt margarine and mix in crumbled Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: turtles "candy"
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters of 3. Cook syrup and milk to 248°. Stir to keep from scorching.
Remove from heat.
Put about 1 teaspoon mixture over each cluster of pecans.
Place 1 small square of Hershey's chocolate bar over each cluster.
When melted, smooth out chocolate.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Place beef roast and soup, onion and salt in crock-pot.
Add water to cover roast.
Cook on High 8 hours.

title: company corn
directions: Heat corn according to package directions.
Drain water and add chilies and cream cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Serve.

title: curry-flavored stew(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cut potatoes, meat and onions into bite-sized pieces.
Place in 2-quart kettle.
Add fat.
Pour in water to almost cover. Boil gently about 20 minutes. Stir in tomato paste or catsup, salt, curry powder and lemon juice.
Cook over high heat about 20 minutes.
Reduce heat and continue cooking about 1 hour.
Serve with hot rice or pilaf.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Brown lightly the garlic and onion with sausage in olive oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, sugar, oregano and basil. Simmer on low heat or crock-pot for approximately 4 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add one egg and a spoon of flour until all gone; beat after each.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring and beat well.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry torte
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Break up and press back into pan.
Cool.

title: ileen's chicken and wild rice soup
directions: Wash rice with cold water; drain and cook in 2 cups water until tender (45 minutes).
Saute celery, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and carrot in butter until tender.
Add 1/2 cup flour and cook and stir 1 minute.
Add broth and chicken.
Bring to a boil and add rice, salt, pepper and Nature's Seasons.
To serve, heat soup mix and stir in 1 cup half and half.
Serve hot.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Cream butter; add gradually, stirring well the egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and cayenne.
Add boiling water slowly.
Stir over boiling water until thick as boiled custard.
Serve immediately.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish (or slightly smaller).
Put chicken over top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add seasoning and tomatoes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and cover bottom and sides with tortillas. Pour beef mixture over tortillas; place layer of tortillas over meat mixture.
Combine the two cheeses and egg.
Pour over tortillas and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle rows of last 5 ingredients diagonally before serving.

title: homemade chili
directions: Lightly brown beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
(Cook in Dutch oven.)

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush enough graham crackers to cover the bottom of a 12 x 8 inch glass dish and have some left over.
Mix water, gelatin, and lemon juice; chill, do not congeal.
Cream cheese and sugar together and mix with chilled gelatin.
Fold in non-dairy whipped topping to thickness desired.
Sprinkle some graham cracker crumbs in a 12 x 8 inch glass dish; pour the mixture over it.
Sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients except bread crumbs and 1 stick oleo. Pour into greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover with the bread crumbs and remaining stick oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut tasting cooky
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Dough will be stiff.
Put it into a long
sheet pan (Pam pan) and bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes
or
until good and brown.	Let it cool and then cut into bars.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken; debone and remove skin.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Crumble cornbread, biscuits and cornflakes in large bowl. Add onions, celery and pepper.
Stir in 4 cups broth.
Add beaten eggs, salt and sage; stir well.
Add more broth until mixture is the consistency of pudding.
Add chicken.
Pour into 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan greased with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour 20 minutes.
Good for Sunday dinner.
Bakes while you're in church.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Rinse and drain chops on paper towel.
Salt and pepper.
Put Coca-Cola in frying pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add chops then add the ketchup on top.
Cook slowly 1 hour or until tender.

title: e-z one dish meal
directions: Slice smoked sausage and brown in saucepan.
Add vegetables. Cover and simmer on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover with cheese; heat until cheese melts.

title: holiday scampi
directions: In a large non stick skillet at medium heat, warm the olive oil.
Add peppers and 2 Tbsp. parsley, scallion and garlic.
Saute until vegetables are tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, lemon juice, vinegar and basil.
Stir fry one or two minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Serves 6.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheeses in plate.
Mix beef, herbs, paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella; spoon on top.

title: green pea salad
directions: Put in casserole in order given.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Clean and cap strawberries.
Slice large.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and juice of 1/2 lemon.
Refrigerate overnight or at least for 2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries and drained pineapple in bottom of square cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries and pineapple.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour melted margarine over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Very good served with a scoop of Cool Whip.

title: chicken salad(the secret is how the chicken is cooked.)
directions: Use a throw-away aluminum pan, large enough for the chicken to spread over the bottom. Spray with Pam. Tear off a piece of aluminum foil for a "lid."

title: chocolate chip-cream cheese bars
directions: Put 1 row of chocolate chip cookies in bottom of square pan, 9 1/2 x 13-inch, and press down.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg altogether.
Put on top of chocolate chip cookies and press down, then add 2nd package of cookies on top.
Add nuts, if you want to.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbara's jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs, baking powder and salt for 5 minutes, then add sugar, vanilla and cake flour. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Flip out onto a wet dish towel and spread with any preserves of your choice or lemon pie filling. Roll in wet dish towel. Leave 5 to 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake or put in blender.

title: diabetic shredded apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Stir until evenly coated.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes more until brown. Top with diabetic ice cream or topping.

title: mom's chocolate cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Roll in balls and drop in bowl of powdered sugar and roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix all other ingredients into butter.
Pat mixture into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Good crust for butterscotch pie.

title: heather's vinaigrette
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: depression cake
directions: In a large saucepan, simmer the first five ingredients for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool 10 minutes. Blend together the remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: cranberry frost
directions: For each serving, place 1 scoop lemon, lime or orange sherbet in tall glass.
Fill with chilled cranberry cocktail.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar (sift); cut in butter until mixture clings.
Press into pan (oblong).
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix well.
Grease pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together (note no flour).
Make into balls (about a teaspoon
of mixture).
Then, on cookie sheet, press down with wet tines of a fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Watch carefully as they brown easily.

title: mountaineer baked beans
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in two tablespoons of butter until onion is tender.
Add ground chuck and brown completely. Add remaining ingredients; stir and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about one hour, stirring frequently to keep from sticking.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Add 1 cup of orange juice and vanilla pudding.
Place nuts in bottom of tube pan.
Pour cake mixture on top.
Bake according to cake package directions or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: best carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook; drain.
Add pepper and onions in large bowl.
Mix last 6 ingredients and marinate for 24 hours or longer.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine other ingredients.
Add yeast and mix well.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Knead on floured board.
Make desired shape and allow to rise again (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Pour into skillet.
Stir while cooking until thick.
It will be lumpy.
Take off stove.
Keep stirring and add vanilla.
It will become smooth.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: sausage corn chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook sausage and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put together in a cloth bag and simmer for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Reheat before serving. Makes 16 (8 ounce) servings.

title: butty-nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add flavoring, flour and nuts.
Chill 1 or 2 hours.
Shape into fingers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Put in crock-pot overnight.

title: turkey corn pone(main dish for 3 to 4)
directions: Fry turkey in a bit of oil until brown and set aside.
Fry onions until soft. Stir in chili powder.
Add tomatoes, corn and green chilies.
Simmer 15 minutes, then put in casserole dish.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter and stir until well blended. Set aside.
Combine chopped pecans, ground graham crackers, confectioners sugar and coconut.
Add butter mixture and mix with a fork until well mixed (mixture will seem rather dry).
Using hands, form into balls about the size of a teaspoon.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over low heat.
Dip balls into mixture using a spoon.
Place on waxed paper to set.

title: greco
directions: Fry onion and green pepper in small amount of oil until glossy.
Brown ground meat in the pan.
Keep moving to prevent burning.
Add mushrooms; remove from heat.
Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and add to mixture.
Add tomato sauce and corn; mix all well.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Can be refrigerated until ready to bake, then grate sharp cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour in a 300° oven.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Blend the cream cheese with 1/2 cup of juice and add to the drained fruit.
Mix the Cool Whip and marshmallows in last. Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: spiced orange tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup boiling water or ice water.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together the cream cheese and sugar until smooth and light.
Beat in the eggs, vanilla and cornstarch only until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in the sour cream until the mixture is well blended.
Pour the mixture into the crust which has been pressed into a 9-inch spring-form pan and prebaked for 8 minutes.
Bake cheesecake for 45 minutes.
Allow the cake to cool in the oven with the door propped slightly open for 3 hours.
Chill.
Top with pie filling if desired.

title: fluffy spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir boiling water into corn meal; continue stirring until mixture is lukewarm.
Blend in 1 tablespoon margarine and the egg yolks.
Stir in buttermilk, salt, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Beat egg whites just until soft peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with margarine and/or syrup.

title: fluffy salad
directions: In bowl, mix cottage cheese, drained fruit and dry jello. Fold in whipped topping.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: corn(frozen)
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Mix everything in bowl; put in pot.
Bring to a boil, then spread on cookie sheet to cool.
Put in freezer bags.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil oleo, brown sugar, white syrup, soda and vanilla mixture for 5 minutes.
Stir and remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla. Pour over the popped corn; stir well to coat.
Put in pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: nestle toll house golden brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, dark brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in Nestle chocolate chips.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into greased pan.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry good and rich dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple and all other ingredients together until completely blended.
Put into a serving bowl; cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in orange juice, shortening and egg.
Blend well.
Add cranberries.

title: shrimp gravy with rice
directions: Clean the shrimp and cut lengthwise; sprinkle with salt and pepper and marinate for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, heat olive oil and pan-fry shrimp until done.
Remove shrimp from pan and to the drippings.
Add onion, tomatoes and garlic and fry until onions are translucent.
Then blend chili powder, cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce and vinegar.
Add this to the onions and tomatoes and add white wine.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and mix well.
Serve over hot rice.

title: boiled custard
directions: In a large double boiler, mix egg yolks and sugar.
Add milk. Place over boiling water, stirring constantly.
Take off stove just before it starts to boil.
Add vanilla.
Cool, then store in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken on bottom of pan.
Grease first with butter, then add cream of celery soup and broth and cream of chicken soup. Then moisten your bread crumbs and put on top.
Add little pats of butter on top of crumbs.
Add more broth, if needed.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add marshmallow topping until desired consistency (almost the whole jar).
Serve with fresh fruit: strawberries, grapes, etc.

title: homemade pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; put in jar and add a little dill, 1 dried pepper and 1 or 2 cloves of garlic.
Boil first 3 items for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.
Before you put seals on jars, boil them in a little pot so they get good and hot.
After sealing the jars, turn them upside down for a few minutes.
They will seal faster.
If some don't seal you can put the whole jar in water (boiling) after tightening the lid.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle almonds on top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Uncover the last 5 minutes.

title: miracle cake
directions: Break eggs into measuring cup and add whipping cream to make 1 cup.
Beat well.
Mix with sugar, flour and almond extract.
Grease 7 x 11-inch pan and line with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Form into small balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate and wax together.
Dip cold balls until 2/3 covered.
Let dry on waxed paper.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, until crumbly, and press in 12 x 8-inch ungreased dish or pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nancy's fried rice
directions: Rinse rice and cook.
(Can use brown rice.)
Fry sausage and take out of pan, leaving meat grease.
Fry onions, celery and carrots in drippings.
Add rice and sausage (cooked earlier).
Add peas or leftovers (corn, beans, whatever).
Mix all together.
Make well in middle and add egg until scrambled.
Mix into rice mixture. Add salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Heat through and serve.

title: grandma ann's potatonick
directions: Grate potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Heat a greased cast-iron pan in oven.
Bake mixture in pan for 10 minutes at 450°.
Lower temperature to 400° and cook until brown on the outside.

title: aunt annie's dill pickles
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together; pour over cukes and dill packed in jars and seal.
Garlic may be added.

title: hoe cake
directions: Stir basic biscuit mix with cold water.
Use bacon fat or margarine to grease a large frying pan.
Spread the batter to fill the pan.
Cook until brown on the bottom, then turn, slipping in a little more grease, and brown the top.
Slice and serve with butter.

title: congo cookies
directions: Mix.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: southern chicken and dumplings
directions: Place hen, water and salt in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer slowly until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool; cut into pieces.
To make dumplings, sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening. Add milk to make a stiff dough.
I sometimes use 1/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup broth.
Roll out thin and cut into squares or strips. Sprinkle lightly with flour and drop into boiling chicken broth. Cover and boil gently for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add cut chicken pieces before serving.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until custard is firm and crust is brown.

title: mock beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in big frypan.
Saute onion and add all other ingredients except rice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: beef jerky
directions: Soak meat in sauces for 20 minutes and drain.
Cook at 150° for 12 hours.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into pieces.
Serve hot or cold.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Mix together soda, baking powder, vanilla and flour.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nuts.

title: grape pie
directions: Remove and save skins from grapes.
Put pulp into saucepan without water and cook on medium heat to separate seeds from pulp. Pour through strainer to remove seeds.
Mix strained pulp with skins.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with top crust and make slots to let steam escape.
I brush the top crust with a little milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve cool or slightly warm, not hot.
Makes a 10-inch pie.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground beef and onions in 10-inch skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: break-away bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Melt Crisco in boiling water.
After melted, add sugar, sifted flour, eggs and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Cover loosely and refrigerate overnight.
Divide mixture in half and roll out like biscuits. Dip each biscuit in melted butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch bread pan.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple pudding
directions: Fill casserole 2/3 full with apple slices.
Top with sugar. Dab with butter.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon, flour and butter and cover apples.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: beef provencale
directions: Trim excess fat off meat.
Remove tendon.
Heat butter in skillet, brown meat well on all sides.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of salt and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Turn meat once during cooking.
Remove meat from skillet and wrap tightly in foil.
Add water to pan.
Heat.
Scrape up brownings. Strain juices.

title: happy change meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine tomato juice, and flour.
Mix them well and add the ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Mix these ingredients until blended, then pour the mixture over the meatballs and bake them for 30 minutes longer.

title: roman long loaf
directions: Insert wooden picks 1 1/2 inches apart into sides of bread loaf, halfway between top and bottom crust.
This is your cutting guide.
Place bread on cutting board.
Cut bread lengthwise, just above row of wooden picks, to make 2 long bread halves.
Remove picks.
Place both halves "bread" side up.
Working carefully, cut each half into 1 1/2-inch slices, stopping 1/2 inch from the bottom crust.
Do not cut through bottom crust.
Combine cheese, margarine, onion and parsley; mix well.
Evenly spread half the mixture on each bread half.
Wrap each bread half in foil.
Place directly on oven rack.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
To serve, carefully remove the aluminum foil and pull off slices.

title: saucy country ribs
directions: Place ribs (single layer) in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°, basting frequently with sauce.

title: apples 'n chicken salad
directions: Combine apple with drained pineapple.
Add chicken, celery and grapes.
Add just enough mayonnaise to hold ingredients together. Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate.
Dip fruits into dip:
bananas, apples, oranges, pineapple, etc.

title: deer hash
directions: Cook deer meat until tender enough to come apart.
Stir until comes apart.
Add sweet potatoes, Irish potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Add 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons corn oil.
Cook slowly until potatoes and onions are done.
Add enough water as needed and cook slowly until liquid is thick like gravy.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in baking pan and sprinkle with tenderizer, liquid smoke, celery
salt,
onion salt and garlic salt on both sides.
Let
stand
in
refrigerator
overnight.
Pour Worcestershire and Tabasco over it.
Cover and bake 5 hours in 275° oven . Add barbecue
sauce and cook another hour.
Can be prepared ahead and reheated for serving.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, brown sugar, evaporated milk, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and can pumpkin together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the cake mix over top.
Pour the melted oleo over top. Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
If not done, bake longer. Serve with or without whipped topping.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cook juice of pineapple (1 cup) with pudding.
After it hardens, add pineapple and let it cool.

title: favorite popcorn balls
directions: Over low heat, melt all ingredients together (except popcorn) until smooth and no sugar crystals remain. Remove from heat and pour over popped popcorn. With hands, form popcorn balls. Put on waxed paper and store in airtight container.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add water and milk slowly. Bring to boil until thick. Serve over hot biscuits or ice cream.

title: ken's apple crunch
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch
casserole dish (can be smaller), line bottom with pie filling.
Fork
butter
into
cake
mix.
Pour cake mix over pie filling.
Bake
at
350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Rub 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine and place vegetables in the bottom.
Brown
the meat and drain it.
Then spread it and the onion
evenly
over the vegetables.
Mix the soup and water and pour
them
over the meat and onion.
Then sprinkle the grated cheese
over
everything.
Place the Tater Tots on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle some cheese
on top.
Return to the oven for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: polynesian fruit dip
directions: Beat well with hand mixer.
Refrigerate.
Good for all kinds of fruit.

title: glazed chicken
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook half of the chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; repeat with remaining chicken.
Meanwhile, stir together cornstarch, broth, marmalade and lemon juice until smooth.
Stir into skillet.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with green onions and pecans.
Serve over rice if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, tear angel food cake in bite size pieces, then mix sour cream, vanilla pie filling and milk.
Mix together and spread over cake pieces.
Then spread Cool Whip over that.
Spread cherry pie filling over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: fudge-rocky road
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips, milk and salt. Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and marshmallows (if desired).
Spread evenly into a wax-paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sear steak on both sides real good after rolling it in flour. Put steak in roaster or large casserole.
Put onions, peppers, butter, salt, sugar and soup over top of steak.
Pour enough boiling water on this to cover.
Cover roaster and bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables together and set aside.
Heat the oil, vinegar and sugar. Cool and then pour
over the vegetables. Best when allowed to set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: hearty supper salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Add mayonnaise just before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: steamed zucchini matchsticks
directions: Cut zucchini and carrots in 2-inch lengths, 1/8-inch wide. Place zucchini sticks on top of carrot sticks in vegetable steamer.
Steam until tender.
Serves 4.
Per Serving:
17 calories.
Saturated Fat:
So light and so tasty, but so fast to fix.

title: hot cheese spread
directions: Using medium blade, put cheese, onions, and jalapeno peppers through a food chopper.
Add mayonnaise, tabasco sauce and salt. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra well; drain.
Cut off tips and stem ends; cut okra crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Roll okra in cornmeal.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels. Sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: grandmother's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients, then add oil, milk and egg and mix well.
Pour into preheated pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: reverend johnson's pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add oil and pumpkin. Measure flour and add remaining ingredients.
Add to liquid ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: instant pistachio jello
directions: Prepare Dream Whip or use already whipped or Cool Whip.
Add handful of marshmallows and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine or butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix in flour, alternating with 7-Up and flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done by inserting a toothpick.
Serves 16 to 24.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese; add jars of cheese.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Grease hands with Crisco and form cheese into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak with flour.
Pound the flour into both sides of the steak.
In a Dutch oven, heat the fat; brown the steak well on both sides.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oriental-style broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli, water chestnuts and onion in hot butter or margarine over medium heat about 10 minutes or just until tender. Turn broccoli occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
In a medium bowl, mix strawberries, glaze and lemon juice. Cut cake in half. Top with strawberries. Serve with whipped topping.
Baking and cooling time:
3 hours.

title: kiwis rellenos(4 servings)
directions: Mix the cottage cheese, cream cheese, the sugar and vanilla. Peel 6 kiwis and cut them in half; put a spoonful of cheese inside.

Peel the remaining kiwi and cube it. Put the cubes in a small pan with the tablespoon of sugar and cook it on the stovetop until the sugar dissolves. Serve 3 halves of kiwi per person and pour the sweetened kiwi chunks over each.

title: midas meat loaf(cooked on grill)
directions: Remove celery leaves and cut celery heart to 8 or 9-inches long.
Wash and dry.
Keep bottom of heart intact.
Gently pull branches apart and sprinkle with salt.
Combine cheese and pimento.
Spread generously between celery branches.
Wrap heart tightly in foil and chill while preparing meat loaf.

title: burger pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick baking mix with water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Pat dough in greased pan with floured hands.
Brown ground beef and salt in skillet; drain.
Crumble over dough.
Sprinkle oregano, pepper and garlic salt over ground beef. Pour Hunt's tomato sauce with cheese over meat mixture.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve hot.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup milk and set aside.
Place 1 cup of milk, 1 cup of sugar and pinch of salt in top of double boiler to scald.
Add well-beaten egg yolks, plus 1/4 cup sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, for approximately 5 minutes.
Add gelatine mixture.
Blend well and let cool.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipped cream and well-beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.

title: hot ham and swiss cheese sandwiches
directions: Melt butter; mix with poppy seed, mustard and onion flakes. Spread on bread; top with ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Heat 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sherburne inn dressing
directions: Mix together tomato soup, sugar, salt, dry mustard, paprika and Worcestershire sauce (a blender works well).
Add oil and vinegar; blend until well mixed.
Serve on tossed salad or fruit. Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat until creamy. Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Gradually add to other mixture. Add vanilla and cinnamon; mix well. Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in greased flat pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
This is great for breakfast or brunch.
Freezes well too.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn cakes
directions: In small bowl, beat egg; pour in meal and enough milk to make it soft.
Add bacon grease and mix.
Fry in hot skillet by tablespoons.
Have skillet good and hot with enough bacon fat to even out.
Takes less than five minutes to make.

title: california bundt cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add bananas, oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple with juice.
Stir to blend well, but do not beat.
Pour onto a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for an hour and 20 minutes.
Cool completely before removing cake from pan.
Glaze.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put a layer of potatoes and onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with some of the flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Repeat layers.
Top with a layer of potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Add enough hot milk to almost cover the potatoes.
Bake, covered, in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: diabetic rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, water, raisins and salt in pan. Bring to a boil. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until cool.
Pour milk into bowl and add pudding mix and nutmeg.
Beat until blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir cooled rice into pudding.
Chill before serving.
Can bake at 300° until pudding browns on top. Taste pudding, if not sweet enough to your taste, add 12 packages Equal.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together all ingredients except dried beef.
Form in a log.
Roll log in chopped dried beef. Chill well before serving.

title: louis abate's tomato sauce
directions: Saute olives, mushrooms, onion and garlic in the oil.
When garlic is brown and onions are sauteed, add the crushed tomatoes, oregano, parsley, basil, salt, pepper, rosemary and the cheese. Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding with crushed pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, then cherries, marshmallows and nuts.
Put in cake pan and put in freezer.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.
Cut in squares.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Mix boiled water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm; add eggs and 4 cups of the flour and mix well.
Add dissolved yeast, then add the other 4 cups of flour.
Let rise 2 to 3 times.
Punch down with a fork each time.
After the last rising, turn onto a floured board.
Roll out until about an inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits. Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple and juice in long glass baking dish, 13 x 9-inches.
Dump 1 can pie filling.
Dump 1 package yellow cake mix.
Melt butter or margarine and dump on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunday eggs and ham
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Melt butter or spray Pam in frying pan and scramble eggs.
Place eggs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop ham and sprinkle on eggs.
Next, layer the mushrooms on top of ham; warm the mushroom soup with sherry and spread over all.
Grate the Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate until required.
Bake at 250° for 50 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 12.
Can be served with coffee cake and fresh fruit.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce; add chicken, okra, celery and green pepper.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place
boned
chicken
on top of rice in greased casserole. Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, molasses, corn syrup and margarine for 5 minutes. Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add soda; mix well.
Have popped corn and peanuts in deep pan.
Pour boiled mixture over.
Mix well to cover.
Put in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan. Remove from heat and stir in cocoa. Beat eggs in small mixer bowl until foamy. Gradually add sugar and vanilla; blend well. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Add chocolate mixture and nuts. Spread 1/2 the chocolate batter into greased 9-inch square pan. Spread cream cheese filling on top of chocolate layer. Drop spoonfuls of remaining filling over cream cheese and use a knife or spatula to swirl the two together. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Remove bone and skin from chicken breasts.
Mix nondairy creamer and egg whites.
Dip chicken breasts in liquid.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Roll chicken in this mixture and place on greased cooking pan.
(Spray with nonstick cooking spray.)
Place 1 teaspoon of margarine on each breast.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until tender and golden brown at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve 1
lime jello in 2 cups hot water.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish and let congeal.
Dissolve 1 lemon jello in 1 cup hot water;
cool.
Add
whipping
cream
and
cottage cheese. Pour over congealed lime jello.	Let congeal.
Dissolve 1 lime jello in 1	cup hot water; add pineapple and nuts.	Pour over congealed lemon jello.

title: texas chile
directions: In large skillet, brown off beef.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer uncovered for one hour.

title: tzatziki(greek yogurt dip, sauce or dressing)
directions: Drain yogurt in cheese cloth in the fridge overnight. Discard liquid.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Beat eggs and add to flour mixture.
Then add sugar. Add enough water or milk to make a dough mixture, not stiff or soft.
Let it set for 1/2 hour.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Fry in deep fat.
Eat hot with honey or mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and roll hot sopaipillas in sugar and cinnamon.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm (110°) water.
Combine sugar, salt, shortening and water in 5-quart bowl.
Stir in 8 cups flour; add yeast and enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth and satiny (5 to 8 minutes).

title: dream pie
directions: Mix the flour and sugar; add melted oleo and pecans.
Work together and put in a deep, ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Let crust cool completely before adding second layer.

title: raisins nut bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Mix cereal and milk in large bowl. Let stand until cereal is softened about 5 minutes.
Beat in oil and egg.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until moistened. Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 18 to 23 minutes.
Yields:
12 muffins.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve with any fresh vegetables.

title: reese's peanut butter bar
directions: Mix all except chocolate chips and milk.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and milk.
Spread on top.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Cut.
Enjoy.

title: coconut almond balls
directions: Combine coconut, milk, almonds and almond extract.
Mix well. Chill.
Shape into balls.
Chill again.
Melt chocolate and shortening over warm water.
Dip balls.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: garlic-roasted halibut
directions: Place vegetables on a baking sheet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with 1/2 rosemary-garlic butter and toss to coat well.
Bake at 450° on upper rack of oven for 20 minutes or until starting to brown.
Stir with spatula and move to bottom rack of oven.

title: rice and chops
directions: Spread 1 cup of rice in a greased or buttered baking dish. Add salt and water.
Mix.
Place pork chops on top of rice. Sprinkle onion soup mix.
Cover with a tight fitting lid or aluminum foil.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours.

title: lemon-basil vegetables and noodles
directions: Cook broccoli flowerets, cauliflowerets, onion, 1/2 cup of stock and lemon peel, in 12-inch skillet over medium heat, 7 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until cauliflowerets are crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining stock and ingredients.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender.

title: goofy cake
directions: Mix together these 4 ingredients and pour over first layer. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake and sprinkle with remaining sugar on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crackers and oleo together in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and press.
Mix together milk, ice cream and pudding with mixer about 2 minutes.
Pour over cracker mix.

title: chocolate ribbon pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and one tablespoon milk in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in half of the whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 2 cups cold milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Mixture will be thick. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Just before serving, spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.

title: scrambled tofu
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil together well.
Warm skillet. Pour in oil.
Pour in all ingredients.
Scramble until brown. Serve hot with toast.

title: lori's hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, margarine, sour cream, cheese and mushroom soup together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and top with French fried onions.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: almond sugar wafers
directions: Put almonds in a blender until finely ground.
Stir together almonds, powdered sugar, water, orange peel and vanilla.
Mix to a stiff paste.
Chill about an hour.
Shape dough into 8 (1 1/4-inch diameter) wafers.
Chill and serve.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine meal, flour and baking powder.
Stir in milk, egg and oil.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking pans.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine in mixing bowl the cantaloupe, milk, egg yolks, flour and 1/4 cup of sugar.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: quick tomato soup cake
directions: Mix
cake as directed on package, substituting soup and water for
the
required
liquid
in directions.
Add eggs, if called for on package.
No additional eggs.
Bake as directed. Good served with cream cheese frosting.

title: tears on your pillow pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat together the butter, brown sugar, eggs, flour and milk until well blended.
Pour the filling into the pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Turn off the oven and leave the pie for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mancuso sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl mix cheese, Bisquick and only 1 package sausage.
In a skillet, brown 1 package sausage.
Drain grease and mix with other ingredients.
With your hands, mix until it forms a large ball.
Form small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°until golden brown.
Serve hot and enjoy!

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over moderate heat until it spins a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Gradually add to the beaten egg whites, beating all the while.
Add vanilla and beat until candy loses its gloss and stands in peaks. Drop by teaspoon. Top with cherries or nuts.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg and mix with a fork until moist.
Spread evenly into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Fold in nuts. Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Place the cream cheese in a bowl.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add to cheese mixture.
Blend all ingredients, except nuts, together. Form mixture into a ball.

title: toasted cubes
directions: Remove crust from French bread and cut into 1-inch cubes. Melt cheeses and margarine. When creamy, fold in beaten egg whites. Dip cubes into mixture and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet AND FREEZE. When frozen, place in a plastic bag and store in freezer. To serve, bake frozen cubes at 450 for about 8 minutes. Serve warm. These taste so good.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt, butter and 2 cups flour.
Add yeast, eggs, potatoes and remaining flour.
Knead.
Roll balls in melted butter.
Place 3 balls in each cup of muffin pan. Let raise.
Bake at 375°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine
melted
butter
and
cocoa,
then add milk and vanilla.
Stir
in the sugar (sift) add sugar in 3 parts, beat until smooth.
If frosting is too thick to spread easily, beat in 1/2 teaspoon milk at a time to get the right consistency.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Bake brownie mix in two 8-inch or smaller pans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix well and bake 40 minutes at 350° in bread pan.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and add picante sauce and tomatoes. Put a layer of picante sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan and then put a layer of three 8 inch tortilla shells, hamburger, tomatoes, picante sauce, sour cream and cheese and repeat again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo over low heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Allow pie to cook (set) 3 or 4 minutes in a 350° oven.
After combining milk and coconut, sprinkle over top of pie and return to oven for 25 minutes.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together.
Serve 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup of hot water.

title: ham and fresh vegetable medley
directions: In 12-inch skillet over high heat, cook peppers, onion, squash and ham in hot salad oil about 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Reduce heat to medium; add water, bouillon, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato wedges; continue cooking until tomatoes are heated through.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a double boiler. Cook over hot water until marshmallows melt. Cool. Mix graham cracker crumbs, pecans, raisins, candied fruits and coconut and pour cooked mixture over this. Pack into Bundt pan or small loaf pans, which have been lined with wax paper. Store in refrigerator. Will stay moist and good for a long time.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean and tear up spinach.
Brown and crumble bacon.
Chop eggs.

title: stuffed tomatoes(yemistes domates)
directions: Slice tops from tomatoes and scoop out center; reserve.
Place tomatoes in baking pan.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil. Add tomato pulp and juices, tomato sauce and water.
Stir with a wooden spoon for one minute.
Add rice, dill, parsley, salt and pepper, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon over low heat until juices are absorbed.
Add pignolia nuts and currants. Remove from stove.
Let mixture cool.
Stuff tomatoes loosely with mixture, leaving a little space on top.
Cover with tops of tomatoes.
Sprinkle top of tomatoes with bread crumbs.
Cover pan with foil or lid.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 1/2 hour longer or until brown.

title: milwaukee pork chops
directions: Sear chops on both sides until brown.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and cook slowly until tender, at least 1 hour.
The longer these simmer the better.
Add more beer later on to keep more juice on.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery until just tender. Blend soup and milk; add to celery in buttered casserole. Mix 2 cups Ritz cracker crumbs with 1/2 cup nutmeats and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over celery. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream eggs and sugar together.
Add oil, flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Fold in 4 cups peeled and diced apples.
Spoon in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 package butterscotch bits over top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: coney islands
directions: Slit wieners lengthwise, not quite to the ends and not quite all the way through.
Cut cheese into chunks about 3 inches long and 1/4-inch square.
Insert the cheese into each slit in the wieners.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each wiener in a spiral fashion and secure each end with a toothpick.
Broil about 15 minutes or until bacon is crispy.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until all is melted.
Take pan from heat and add Rice Krispies. Mix well.
Press mixture into well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all this together.
Put in baking dish.

title: roast marinate
directions: Mix all ingredients and baste roast.
I like to take a knife and prick meat all over so that marinate can penetrate through meat.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Bake and baste with sauce.

title: elephant ears
directions: Break bread dough in 1/2.
Stretch out or roll out in a large circle.
Heat a large frying pan with 1/2 stick butter; place bread in pan.
Cook on both sides.
When bread is done, put on a plate and sprinkle with mixed cinnamon and sugar.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Flour dough in hand; form biscuits.
Cook in iron skillet at 425°.

title: toasted oat treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine in large microwave bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows. Toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth. Stir after 45 seconds.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; stir to blend.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve in hollowed out loaf of French bread; use hollowed out section to make bread cubes for dipping or pour into your favorite bowl and dip with chips and crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan. Bake at 375° until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: garden casserole
directions: Lightly brown onions and beef in fat, stirring constantly. Add green pepper, celery, carrots, tomatoes, seasonings and sugar; simmer for 20 minutes. Pour into 2-quart casserole; top with potatoes. Brush lightly with butter or margarine. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Garnish with parsley.

title: cranberry marshmallow cream
directions: Mix together cranberries, pineapple and sugar in bowl.
Fold marshmallows into whipped cream.
Fold cream mixture into cranberry mixture.
Chill.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook and brown together ground beef, onions and cabbage.
Add celery, beans, tomatoes, salt, pepper, chili powder and water to cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls with a dollop of mashed potatoes floated in center.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion. Drain. Cook macaroni. Combine all ingredients. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quick oatmeal cake
directions: Put under broiler 2 or 3 minutes.
Topping should be bubbly and slightly brown when done.

title: taralli (italian bread sticks)
directions: Mix eggs, oil, salt, fennel and pepper.
Dissolve sugar in water and also the yeast.
Add this and flour to egg mixture.
Work dough until you can work with your hands.
Form into sticks.
You then have to boil them until they float to the top of the water. Put bread sticks right on racks to bake.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Switch level of racks.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pizza like snacks
directions: Remove casing and brown sausage until almost done. Then add ground beef & brown together until done. Drain well. In skillet, mix in cubed cheese, oregano & garlic salt. Cover & keep heat on low. Stir occasionally until cheese is melted. Cool. Spread browned mixture on pieces of rye bread. Then broil for approximately 4 minutes. Serve hot.

title: kosher dills
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut in half lengthwise.
Combine garlic, salt, water and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Remove garlic and place 4 halves into each hot sterilized jar.
Pack cucumbers into jars, adding 2 sprigs dill weed and 4 peppercorns to each jar.
Pour boiling vinegar mixture over cucumbers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Cover jars at once with metal lids and screw on metal bands.
Process jars in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 7 pints.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: creamy broccoli cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in medium bowl.
Serve with vegetable dippers and assorted crackers, if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: maureen's caramel popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, Karo and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Butter a large bowl.
Combine popped corn and nuts.
Pour Karo mixture over popped corn.
Break into chunks or shape into balls.

title: mexican fiesta treat
directions: Combine cheese; sprinkle half of it in 8-inch square pan, forming a bottom layer.
Combine eggs and salsa.
Pour over cheese; top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°, until golden and bubbly.
Serve hot with tortilla chips, or allow to cool; cut into squares and store in refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate pieces, Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, onion, bacon, raisins and walnuts. Just before serving, combine last 4 ingredients.
Pour over salad, toss and serve.
Per serving:
178 calories and 4 g fat.

title: really easy totally awesome brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put unsweetened chocolate and margarine in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for two minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Put cereal in large bowl and pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Gently stir until cereal is thoroughly coated.
Spread on wax paper and let dry.
Pour powdered sugar into brown paper bag and fold top back and keep it open wide.
Pour in coated cereal, close sack and shake until all cereal is coated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, green pepper, onion, milk and package of meat loaf mix all together in a bowl.
Put in a baking pan and shape.
Mix 2 packages gravy mix with 2 cups water. Pour over meat loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, remove excess grease and slice meat loaf into slices, so the meat will get done.
Cover and bake 1 hour more.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and drain. Add rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water with 1 teaspoon baking soda. In the morning, remove any floating beans.
Using the same water, add all ingredients as well as the meaty ham bone.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for a few hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Cream the butter, margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until smooth and creamy. Add the flour, beating well.
Put the vanilla in and mix well.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Pour batter in pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 cup chopped dates and add soda.
Let stand while the following is mixed in the usual manner: sugar, butter, egg, flour, vanilla, salt, baking powder and nuts. Add these ingredients to the date mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all in a large bowl.
Toss lightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: mighty good chilli
directions: To browned and drained hamburger, add next 5 ingredients, mixing as you go.
Add seasoning salt, chili powder and garlic powder to your taste.
Cook over
low heat until onions and celery are done, stirring thoroughly and often.

title: orange oatmeal bread
directions: Grease 2 small or 1 large loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix together and soak first 4 ingredients for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cremes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into teaspoon size balls and place on pan or plate.
Refrigerate them, then eat!
(No baking!)

title: thirteen bean soup mix
directions: Measure 1/4 cup each: dried black-eyed peas, small red beans, cranberry beans, cow peas pigeon peas, baby lima beans, red kidney beans, pink beans, pink bans, navy beans, black beans, pinto beans and yellow split pea and green split peas.

title: steve's venison chili
directions: Brown venison in skillet and drain.
Brown onions in skillet and add with meat to cooking pot.
Add broth and tomatoes and bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer and add spices.
Simmer for an hour; add beans and hominy and simmer another hour.
(Ground beef can be substituted if necessary, lean chuck or round is better.)

title: wet coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is done, punch holes in cake while still hot.
Pour on cream of coconut, then pour on sweetened condensed milk.
Let stand overnight.
Spread on Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: three-bean and wild rice casserole
directions: About 1 3/4 Hours Before Serving:
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook carrots, onion, mushrooms and salt until vegetables are golden.

title: peggy's hot sauce
directions: Put first six ingredients into blender along with the juice drained from the canned whole tomatoes.
Chop into small chunks. Then add tomatoes and tomato sauce and blend to desired texture. Keeps well in the refrigerator, if it lasts.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cranberry and apple crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, sugars and butter in a food processor; pulse until mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: reese cup cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Press onto cookie sheet pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Pour over top of peanut butter mixture.

title: seafood squares
directions: Stir biscuit mix and onion powder together in bowl.
Add milk, mix to form a soft ball.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes to partially cook.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add cream, salt and pepper.
Combine with cheeses, shrimp and crab.
Pour over top of hot biscuit mixture and return to oven.
Bake 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve warm.
Garnish with sprigs of dill or parsley and tomato wedges.
Makes 54 squares.
May be made ahead.
Cover and reheat.

title: salami stack-ups
directions: Soften the cream cheese and blend with green onions.
Make 5 stacks of salami and spread cream cheese mixture between slices. Chill thoroughly, then cut each stack into equal wedges.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add fruit cocktail and 1 egg. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan.
Drain off grease.
Cut up veggies and mix in with cooked sausage; add a touch of salt and as much teriyaki sauce as desired.
Mix well.
Lay egg roll wrapper out flat; mix the water and flour to make a paste and smooth around edges of wrapper.
Put tablespoon of mixture into wrapper and roll it up.

title: french bread casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut bread 1-inch thick and put in pan.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients except butter.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.
Dot with butter.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with your favorite flavor of syrup. This is a wonderful brunch dish; especially nice because the preparation can be in advance.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Place bread and sausage in a greased 10 x 13 inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over top of bread and sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be prepared and refrigerated uncooked overnight. Yield:
8 to 12 servings.

title: fruit cobbler #3
directions: Melt butter in	a
2-quart
dish.
Mix together, but do not stir, 3/4
cup
sugar,
flour and milk.
Pour over butter. Mix together, but do
not
stir,
fruit juice and 1 cup sugar. Pour over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender; set aside 1 cup broth to cool. Remove bone and skin from chicken.
Return meat to broth in boiler.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put the cup of cooled broth in bowl.
Add enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut in about 2-inch squares. Add to boiling broth in boiler.
Cook for a few minutes until dough has time to cook.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let set 5 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Stir in 6 ounce package chocolate chips and 4 ounce bar of German chocolate, grated.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: kornbread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into hot iron frying pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use 2 or 3 cups of boiled chicken or turkey.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix with sour cream and soup.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Crush crackers with a little melted butter and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake until hot at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in noodles.
Bake in a shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: bavarian chowder-cabbage
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown and cook sausage. Drain grease. Cook carrots and caraway in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8. Serve with corn bread!

title: banana cake
directions: Use medium size bowl and beater.
Mash bananas and add sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Blend together.
Add slightly beaten eggs, followed by rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into two 9-inch pans and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: 3 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling; stir. Remove from heat; add other ingredients, stirring until melted. Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan lined with waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble the ground beef in bottom of 8-inch baking dish.
Over this, pour the soup.
Sprinkle with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese boats
directions: Cut frankfurters lengthwise almost to bottom.
Place 1 strip of cheese in each frankfurter.
Wrap each with a slice of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Place cut side down on rack or broiler pan.
Broil at 550° with tops about 5 inches from heat, turning when bacon is crisp, about 15 minutes.

title: hamburger and corn pie
directions: Start oven 10 minutes before baking; set to moderately hot (425°).
Heat bacon fat in skillet, add ground beef and onions. Stir and cook until meat is separated.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and flour blended with water smoothly.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes and stir constantly until thickened.
Heat butter in saucepan, add corn, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook constantly for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour a little more than half the corn into well buttered 9 or 10-inch glass pie pan.
Place in oven and cook 15 minutes. Remove quickly from oven and add hot hamburger mixture and rest of corn.
Lay quarter rings of green peppers around edges.
Return to oven, bake 15 to 20 minutes or until bottom and top are brown. Serves 4 to 5.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil and drain.
Coarsely chop tomatoes and add to meat, including the juice from tomatoes.
Add water and 4 beef bouillon cubes.
Simmer this for about 1/2 hour.
Add canned vegetables, including the water they're packed in.
Add pasta.
Let cook over low heat until pasta is tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray a 12 or 14-inch pizza pan with Pam.
Slice cookie dough and lay on pan.
Press to cover pan with cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool on a wire rack until completely cold.
Mix Philadelphia cream cheese, cherry juice and sugar until smooth.
Spread over cookie to edge.

title: french toast
directions: Mix
eggs, salt and milk in pie pan.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Dip
bread
quickly in egg mixture.
Brown on one side and
sprinkle with cinnamon.
Turn and brown other side. Serve immediately.
Try
applesauce
or
sour cream on French toast for a change.

title: salmon noodle ring
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Mix lightly.
Grease ring pan with butter.
Pour into pan.
(May keep in refrigerator several hours.)
Set ring in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff; fold in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in crackers, baking powder and walnuts.
Bake in well greased 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and coconut.
Bake in well-greased tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan while making sauce.

title: pasta salad
directions: Place first three ingredients in bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Now mix all together and chill.

title: whole wheat oatmeal hot cakes
directions: Combine egg, milk, oil and honey.
Add Pancake Mix and stir until batter is blended, but still slightly lumpy.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter onto hot, lightly greased griddle.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 5 - 7 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, onion, garlic, bacon drippings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add flour to thicken, bacon bits, seasoning.
Cook additional 5 - 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: snicker cookies
directions: Beat together butter, peanut butter and sugars until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add to peanut mixture, beating until smooth. Shape 1 teaspoon dough around Snickers bar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick and easy patties
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into patties. Lay in long baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes; drain.
Turn each pattie over.
Bake 20 minutes more; drain again if necessary.

title: winter vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat. Add carrots, parsnips, celery, onions, garlic and thyme.
Cook, stirring frequently, until slightly softened, 5 minutes.
Add barley and rice; stir to coat.
Stir in broth, 2 cups water, the potatoes and tomato.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer, covered, skimming and stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Stir in spinach, salt and pepper; simmer, covered, 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream together softened butter and shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and flavoring. Alternate flour and milk, mixing well.
Put in tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Let set 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely before covering.

title: tuna balls
directions: Mix together in a bowl the tuna, egg, corn meal and crackers. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Deep fry in hot oil about 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 (1-inch) balls.
Kids love these.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in unsalted water until almost tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, cook 2 minutes; add remaining ingredients, simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Serve hot or cold.	This is a dish, that can be made ahead of time and will last when stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: jello delight
directions: Melt jello and cheese with boiling water; add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a chilled pan and chill.
Serve as a dessert or with meal.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, powdered sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in half.
Blend food coloring into 1 half.
Shape teaspoon of dough from each half into 4-inch ropes.
For smooth, even ropes, roll them back and forth on lightly floured board. Place ropes side by side; press together lightly and twist. Complete cookies one at a time.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Curve top down to form handle of cane.
Bake 9 minutes.
Sprinkle cookies with candy-sugar mixture.
Remove.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Put oatmeal in mixing bowl.
Stir in melted butter.
Blend eggs and sweetener.
Add to oatmeal.
Mix milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to the oatmeal-egg mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 72 cookies.

title: snicker snack
directions: Place graham crackers side by side in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine butter and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Immediately pour over graham crackers.
Spread to coat.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let chips stand 1 minute.
Spread.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Lightly press peanuts into chocolate.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: meal on kabobs
directions: Mix tomato juice, vinegar and seasonings.
Place meat in a shallow glass dish; pour tomato juice mixture over meat.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Remove meat from marinade; reserve marinade.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cool bread and then break coarsely.
Mix together onions, tomatoes, peppers, eggs and bacon.
Add mayo, then cornbread, trying not to break cornbread too much.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute garlic (minced) in oil; add tomatoes.
Bring to a boil. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer to desired thickness.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion, seasonings and 6 cups water in soup kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Strain meat and skim off excess fat.
Add meat and vegetables; cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix for 2 minutes on high.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 20 minutes and turn out on rack.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store.
Mix 3 teaspoons of tea mixture to one cup of hot water.

title: fannie may cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, Hershey's syrup and flour to the margarine and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake the crust and let it cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese. Put it on the cool crust.
Put on the drained pineapple and start layering the rest of the fruit.

title: apricot, nut and barley stuffing for wild duck or goose
directions: Saute the apricots, raisins and nuts in the butter, stirring frequently, until the dried fruit has softened and the nuts are lightly browned.
Sprinkle in the cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in the barley and salt lightly.
Stuff into wild duck or goose. Makes 2 cups.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Mix together. Stuff bird and bake as per directions.

title: pot pie
directions: Take about 2 cups flour to make moist dough, Crisco (size of egg), about 1/2 cup milk, the baking powder and the salt.
Mix all together; roll about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares; let set for about 10 minutes.
Add to cook, soup bone, cooking beef, chicken or ham until done.
Add pot pie.

title: orange fluff
directions: Bring the water to a boil.
Add the pudding mix and jello; do so gradually with a whisk.
Cook until clear.
Cool overnight. Add well drained oranges, Cool Whip and jello mixture together, folding together gently.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: three bean chili
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook over high heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water until plump.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to measure 1/2 cup.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in reserved liquid. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries, salt and water on stove.
When starting to boil, add soda and cook 10 minutes or until all cranberries have popped.
Add sugar and jello and stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows while hot so they can dissolve.
Remove from stove and let cool.
Add celery, apples and nuts.
This needs to be stirred occasionally until it jells as the ingredients tend to float.
Put into container to store; the flavor improves each day.

title: mom's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating in creamy mixture.
Add crushed pecans, coconut, crushed vanilla wafers and milk.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in oil; add garlic and onion.
Mix together chili powder, flour, salt, pepper, oregano and cumin seed and add to meat mixture.
Add water and lime juice.
Simmer, covered, for 1 to 2 hours.
Add beans if desired.
Serve.

title: perpetual muffins
directions: Pour water over cereals.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix eggs into cereal.
Add oil and dry ingredients and buttermilk last.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain and rinse in cold water. Drain again. Be sure all water is off. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes. Stir while cooking. Seal in sterilized jars.

title: cubed steak haystacks
directions: Prepare hash browns as directed on package; set aside.
Melt shortening in another large skillet.
Place cubed steak in skillet over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until brown. Remove skillet from heat.
Season steak with salt and spread each steak with catsup.
Top each steak with 1/2 cup cooked hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Return to heat, cover and cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: corn bread(healthful eating)
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with a spoon.
Bake in a 9-inch round Teflon pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the sugars and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Rinse raisins in strainer with hot water.
Stir in raisins, oats, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy broccoli sauce
directions: Mix well.
Pour over hot or cold cooked broccoli.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: In medium bowl, whip egg whites, then set aside.
Make sure egg whites are very stiff; this makes stiff ice cream.
In large mixing bowl, mix egg yolks, sugar, can milks and vanilla flavoring.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in egg whites.
Put Oreos in gallon size Ziploc bag and crush with hammer.
Fold Oreos into batter.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill to line with whole milk.
Makes 1 1/2 gallon freezer full.
Yum yum.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook pie shell.
Cool.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Combine with milk in large heavy saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add to milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
