Stir in vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Thicken.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Add Never Fail Meringue.
Bake at 425° until meringue is brown.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Spread ribs in shallow baking dish.
Brown in 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Spoon sauce over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Stir ribs and sauce every 20 minutes or so.
Water may be added if sauce becomes too thick.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine according to package directions.
While fettucine cooks, heat butter and cream in small saucepan until butter melts.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Keep warm over low heat.
Drain fettucine, return to pan and pour sauce over noodles.
Toss gently until noodles are well coated.
Serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt oleo and grease.
Add Accent, salts and Worcestershire. Sprinkle on cereal, Bugles, pretzels, Fritos, peanuts and cashews. Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hug recipe
directions: Extend arms and wrap them around each other.
Clean your minds and take a good look at each other.
Pull yourselves together and mix well.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bring milk, grits and 1/2 cup butter to boil, stirring constantly. Continue cooking until consistency of oatmeal, about 5 to 8 minutes. Remove from heat and add salt and pepper. Beat well with a slotted spoon. Add cheese, chilies and 1/3 cup butter, stirring carefully until butter is melted and blended. Pour into prepared casserole dish; sprinkle evenly with grated Parmesan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix crabmeat, cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Spread in small greased casserole.
Melt margarine and mix in bread crumbs.
Spread over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: all together fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: In skillet, over low heat, melt oleo, then stir in rice.
Add soup, bouillon cube, water and mushrooms.
Pour everything into a greased casserole dish when well mixed.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: traditional maple walnut candies
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate and a 2 x 2-inch square of wax.*
By hand or food processor, mix sugar and milk.
Add walnuts and extract.
Roll into small balls.
Place on waxed paper.
With a toothpick, pick up a ball and dunk into chocolate mixture. Return ball to wax paper.

title: raisin-pecan pie
directions: Make crust for 9-inch pieplate.
Bake at 450° for 3-5 minutes. Remove pastry from oven and cool completely.

title: orange chantilly
directions: Line a strainer with a double layer of cheesecloth.
Place yogurt in the center; let drain for 1 hour.
Place orange juice in a small pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes, swirling the pan occasionally, until a very thick syrup remains.
There should be about 2 tablespoons.
Reserve.

title: saucy short ribs
directions: Cut beef into 4 pieces.
Brown on all sides in hot oil in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
If sauce becomes too thick, add small amount of water. Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Stir cream cheese and mayonnaise until softened.
Add soup, garlic powder and Season-All.
Drain.
Wash and chop shrimp.
Add the shrimp to the mixture and season to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat 1 minute. Stir dry ingredients together. Alternately add the dry ingredients and the berries to the batter, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla; beat 1 minute. Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake. When cake is done, it can be sprinkled with powdered sugar while still warm or iced with vanilla frosting when cool. Cake flavor improves if it is allowed to mellow 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in loaf pans for 45 minutes at 325°. Put foil on top and cook 45 minutes longer or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix well. Roll to 1/8-inch. Let dry for about 2 hours, turning so both sides can dry, then roll and slice as thinly as possible. Drop in boiling chicken broth. Cook about 30 minutes. Beef is good also.

title: tarts lemon pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in container of an electric blender; process 3 minutes or until smooth.
Add butter; process 30 seconds.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt. Yield: one 9-inch pie.

title: hunter's favorite burrito pie
directions: In hot salad oil, fry 1 tortilla at a time, about 30 seconds on each side.
Remove to paper towel to drain.
Preheat oven to 350° Cook ground beef, onion, and garlic until browned.
Remove from heat and stir in chiles, refried beans, taco sauce, and salt.
In a 9 inch pie plate, place 1 tortilla, top with1/4 of the bean mixture, and 1/4 of the cheese.
Repeat 3 times.
Bake 30 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded lettuce, and diced tomato.
(Makes 6 servings.)

title: chicken with rice
directions: Boil the chicken; cool.
Take off bone.
Wash rice and soak for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and rice to broth.
Combine onion; cook on low heat for approximately 2 hours.

title: grandma b's corn flake candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and cream.
Cook to soft ball stage or until 236° on candy thermometer.
Add corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Spread in greased pan.
Cool and cut in bars. Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: sweet and sour jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Mix all other ingredients; add Jell-O and refrigerate.

title: mini chicken meat loaves(microwave oven)
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Divide evenly into cups of a 6-cup microwave-safe muffin pan.
Microwave (High) 5 to 6 minutes, until done.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Remove gently from pan. Makes 3 servings.
Freezes well.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in a
baking
dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Mix
flour	and sugar together;
cut in margarine.	Pour over and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hershey's double mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan. Spread mint cream layer on cake.
Chill.
Pour chocolate topping over dessert; cover.
Chill.

title: quick sourdough bread
directions: Grease a large bowl.
In another bowl mix all ingredients and make a stiff batter.
Place dough in a greased bowl and brush some oil on top of the dough.
Cover with cloth or waxed paper and sit in a warm place until it doubles.
Do not refrigerate.
Push down dough and knead well.
Divide into 3 or 4 loaves.
Knead each loaf 8 to 10 times.
Place in greased pans.
Oil top of each loaf. Cover and let rise until about double.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans; brush with butter or margarine.

title: crustless asparagus quiche
directions: Heat margarine and onions.
In a bowl, combine onions with asparagus, milk, eggs, 1 ounce cheese and seasonings.
Grease a 7-inch pie plate and pour in mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add gradually to egg mixture, blending thoroughly. Stir in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: champagne punch
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients well.
Add sherbet just before serving.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix puddings with milk.
Set just a minute and then add Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Add half of mixture, another layer of graham crackers and remaining mixture. Top with layer of graham crackers.

title: black walnut ice box tea cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into rolls and wrap; then chill. Cut 1/4 inch slices for baking.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese in a mixer.
Add eggs to cheese, one at a time; mix.
Add sugar and vanilla.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Toss together with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute
onion
and
mushrooms
in margarine.
Wash rice. Put rice
and soup in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.	Pour onion and mushrooms on top and stir.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: aunt jean's marchetti
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Cook noodles and arrange in layers, starting with noodles, 1/2 sauce, 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375°.
Can be made a day ahead and baked next day.

title: grits and cheese
directions: Add grits to salted boiling water.
Turn down heat and cook for 30 minutes with lid on, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add the butter and eggs; stir until smooth.
Add cheese and mix well; pour into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let first three ingredients reach room temperature. Mix cream cheese and butter and add sugar gradually, continuing to beat. Add eggs one at a time. Add flour slowly while continuing to beat. Add vanilla last. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and ground peppers and juice for 15 minutes.
Stir often.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Use 3 heaping tablespoons per cup of hot water.
Makes a bunch.

title: mabel's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add milk and other ingredients and stir, then place pieces of bread in baking dish.
Pour liquid over and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pot roast ala orange(muchacho ala noranja)
directions: Season previously the 3 pounds of pot roast with the pepper, lemon juice and onion.

Put the cut pieces of bacon to saute in a skillet of 8-inches without grease until it is brown and toasted. Put the pot roast in a pressure cooker with 2 chicken cubes, cook during 30 minutes when the pressure cooker starts to whistle. After these steps, take the pot roast and put it in a deep skillet, about 9 1/2-inches in size.
Add the Maggi sauce, orange juice, 1 cup of chicken broth, 1 cup of water and flour.
Mix and let these ingredients thicken.
When it is ready to serve, enhance this dish by putting the tiny pieces of bacon on top.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and butter or margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour (mixed with salt) alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
When cake is removed from oven, pour over glaze.

title: spicy garlic shrimp and spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In medium skillet, heat olive oil.
Add shrimp, lemon juice, garlic, lemon peel and cayenne pepper.
Stir- fry until shrimp is opaque. In medium bowl, blend cornstarch into chicken broth and pour over shrimp.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.
Add spaghetti and parsley; toss to coat.
Heat through.
Arrange on a warm serving platter and serve immediately.

title: guacamole mexicano
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.

title: grape jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Mix in other ingredients.
Chill until set in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: durkee chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Boil until done.
Drain well.
Mix bottle of Durkee and bottle of water.
Stir until blended.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 20 or 30 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: carolina chews
directions: *If using plain flour add 1 tsp. soda, 1/2 tsp. baking powder and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Cream together first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
In 13 x 9 greased and floured pan, bake for 45 minutes on 300°.
Puffy at first.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut in squares.
Yield:
approximately 3 doz.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix in order given; pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until firm and serve.

title: nutty meat loaf(diabetic - meat)
directions: Mix ingredients, using half of the tomato juice.
Shape meat loaf and place in pan.
Pour remaining tomato juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Heat all but corn over low heat until mixed well.
Add corn and stir.
Put in a 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pig eatin good cake
directions: Mix cake; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool, then ice.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Butter casserole dish.
Alternate layers of spaghetti, cheese and tomatoes.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and oregano.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Combine noodles, tuna, chicken or turkey leftovers, mayonnaise, onion, peppers and salt. Blend soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Put into casserole. Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: bethlehem academy inn's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water until tender.
Drain. Mash and drain again.
Add butter, beaten egg yolks, cream of mushroom soup and salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into squash mixture.
Fold in squash mixture.
Place mixture in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle meat lightly with garlic powder.
Put into ovenproof casserole (large).
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 2 hours, until meat is very tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: southwestern pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet or 12-inch pizza pan.
Press crust onto sheet or pan and pinch edge to form rim.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts from bread and flatten with a rolling pin.
Blend cheeses and egg to workable consistency and spread evenly on each slice of bread.
Place an asparagus spear on each slice, roll and secure with toothpicks.
Dip in melted butter to coat thoroughly, place on cookie sheet and freeze.

title: blender gazpacho
directions: Blend thoroughly in blender or food processor.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Top each serving with a dollop of sour cream.
Serves nine 2/3-cup servings.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Mix butter, sugar and Bisquick until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough forms; beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoons, 2-inches apart, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make a shallow well in center of each with back of spoon; fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake until golden, 10 to 15 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with glaze.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook 3 cups of milk and rice in a double boiler.
When milk is absorbed, add sugar and remaining cup of milk.
Cook until milk is absorbed.
Serve warm.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni and vegetables in a large bowl, then add water, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Mix well; refrigerate.
Garnish with sliced eggs.
(Before garnishing, add salt and pepper to taste.)

title: hot punch
directions: Bring cider, brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes, then add other juices.

title: gleasons
directions: Mix together into dough.
Roll out onto floured board and cut into different shapes.
Drop into broth.
Do not boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
This is an Indian dish, to be used instead of noodles.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make yellow cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce thoroughly with large fork. Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; drizzle slowly over cake. Mix instant pudding as package directs; spread over cake. Refrigerate until just before serving (overnight is okay).
Slice strawberries and banana over cake.
Spread whipped topping over cake; cut and serve.

title: hawaiian sausage casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice if necessary to equal 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Arrange pineapple chunks, sweet potatoes and sausage in 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually blend in reserved pineapple juice mixture.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; stir in butter.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pull aparts
directions: Place in bottom of Bundt pan the nuts and frozen dinner rolls. Mix brown sugar and butterscotch pudding together (do not cook). Sprinkle over rolls.
Pour over melted butter and then sprinkle the white sugar and cinnamon over butter.
Cover with cloth and let stand 8 hours to rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes in pan.
Serve.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Stir peanut butter chips, butter and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over very low heat until melted and smooth.
Add cereal and stir until blended. Remove from heat. Drop level tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on waxed paper.
Press into flat 2-inch round cookies.
Let stand at room temperature 20 minutes or until firm. Spoon jelly into cup and stir until runny. Drizzle on cookies, then sprinkle with nuts. Store, airtight, at room temperature.

title: creamed spinach crunch
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix with cream cheese, margarine, water chestnuts, mushrooms and onions.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes in a 2-quart casserole.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Pour milk into blender. Heat strawberry juice to boiling.
Add juice and gelatin to blender.
Stir 1 minute, then liquefy.
Add strawberries, egg yolks, sugar and food coloring.
Liquefy.
Add cream and crushed ice and frappe.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook until thick; add 1 lump of butter after cool.
Put into 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients on flat dish.
Sprinkle taco sauce on top. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pocket stew for 12
directions: Each person brings a vegetable or bouillon cubes.
The water is boiled in a large pot.
Everything is cut up and placed in boiling water.
The stew is done after 35 minutes of boiling.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat.
Makes 2 small or 1 large loaf.
Bake 1 hour in a moderate oven.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Boil chicken; cube.
Cook noodles until done; drain.
Pour soup and water over noodles.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake biscuits as directed, cutting cooking time in half.
Pour noodles and chicken into casserole dish; layer biscuits in a single layer on top.
Bake for second half of biscuit directions.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: swiss cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients, except Swiss cheese, in blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Add cheese, a little at a time, until all blended.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Can also use bananas.

title: whoopie pie cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add milk and 1/2 vanilla. Mix cocoa and water together.
Add to oil and sugar mixture. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Bake on 2 cookie sheets with sides at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (11 x 15-inch cookie sheets).

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Stir soup and cheese together, adding milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg.
Mix until well blended; pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over the soup mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger in oleo.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy chocolate bars
directions: Bake cookie dough according to directions on package.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Spread on cookie base.

title: cheese vegetable chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine broth, Worcestershire sauce, basil, thyme and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in carrots and onion.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 6 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: carrot soup(colorful and surprisingly good)
directions: Slice all vegetables and place in large pot.
Add chicken stock and bring to boil.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, then puree in batches.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and hint of cumin or hot pepper sauce.

title: banana pudding
directions: Sprinkle bananas with lemon juice after they have been sliced. Line a 1-quart casserole dish with a layer of vanilla wafers. Top with a layer of bananas.
Set aside.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add flour, salt and sugar.
Stir in oil and milk.
Mix well with fork.
Press the dough into the pie pan, using a small amount at a time.
Flute edges and bake at 450° until golden brown.
This pie crust can also be used for baked fruit pies.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie crust.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Line a 12-inch pizza pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil; grease and set aside.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate about 30 to 45 minutes before serving.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water in a large mixing bowl.
Melt marshmallows in top of double boiler with 1/4 cup boiling water and add to gelatin mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add whipping cream and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased mold.
Refrigerate until set. Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: cheese stix
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Roll out and cut into strips 4 inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat, garlic and onion together.
Crush 1/2 bag nacho chips (or Doritos) in bottom of large casserole dish.
Put half of meat mixture on crushed chips.
Mix soups together, put half soup mixture on top of meat.
Put one cup cheese on top of soup. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Simmer carrots until done, but firm.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over hot carrots.
Let stand overnight. Refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: broiled lemon chicken
directions: Preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
In 1-quart saucepan, over low heat, heat butter or margarine, lemon juice, salt, sugar and pepper until butter is melted.
Place chicken, skin side down, on large broiling pan.
Broil 20 minutes.
Baste with butter mixture frequently to moisten and add flavor to chicken pieces.

title: plum jam
directions: In a large saucepot, put washed plums and barely cover with water.
Cook until skins break open and fruit is tender.
Pour into a colander and remove seeds and peelings.
Measure the amount of juice and pulp; add equal amount of sugar and bring to a boil. Stir constantly to avoid sticking on bottom.
Simmer until mixture is thick enough to put in hot, dry jars.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: You will need 1 unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.

title: tex mex corn muffins
directions: Heat ungreased muffin pans in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Combine cornmeal, soda and salt in a bowl.
Stir in next five ingredients.
Make a well in the center.
Combine milk, corn and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moist.
Spoon into muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, salt, butter and milk for 6 minutes, then pour boiling syrup into a large bowl over the chocolate chips, German chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Beat until chocolate is all melted and pour into pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in tin box.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: *Choose one of the meats or use a mixture to make a pound.

title: eggplant supreme
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Place in cold water for 10 minutes. Drain and cook with fresh water, onion and celery until tender. Drain.
Blend soup and milk into eggplant.
Add pepper, cheese, bread crumbs and salt.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with partially cooked bacon and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: almond jello
directions: Dissolve gelatine and sugar in hot water.
Add evaporated milk and almond extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into rectangular shape pan.
Place pan in refrigerator to set. Cut jello in diamond shapes or cubes.
Spoon mandarin oranges or fruit cocktail over jello cubes when ready to serve.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: corn relish
directions: Drain corn; reserve liquid.
Toss corn with onion, pepper and pimento.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put over cole slaw or macaroni.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening.
Add milk.
Roll out with rolling pin to about 1/2-inch thick or thicker. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cantaloupe bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
If batter seems too thick, add additional juice.
Grease and flour loaf pans; bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Melt butter over top and sprinkle 10x sugar on top.

title: bunco punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large container. Place in freezer several hours until frozen.
Serve and enjoy! Mixture is "slush" consistency when ready.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 350-425 degrees until brown. Makes 6.

title: penuche icing
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in Milnot until it comes to a boil. Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add 1 3/4 to 2 cups sifted confectioners sugar.
Beat until spreading consistency.
If too stiff, add a few drops hot water.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms and place in glass or earthenware bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cherry o'cream cheese parfaits
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip until fluffy.
Gradually add milk.
Continue beating until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: cranberry orange cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the sugar and margarine until creamy.
Stir in the milk, eggs and grated orange peel.
Gradually add the flour, uncooked oats, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Fold in the cranberries.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes; cool.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch square pans.
Beat eggs and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add fruit cocktail, flour, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended.
Spread in pans. Sprinkle with coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While hot, drizzle with glaze.

title: shorting bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 25 minutes at 450°.

title: easy but good peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet, press crisscross with a fork. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 1 minute before lifting from cookie sheet.

title: holiday beef rib-eye roast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine garlic, salt, pepper and rosemary; press evenly on roast.
Place on rack in shallow pan.
Insert meat thermometer so bulb is centered in thickest part.
Do not add water or cover.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes per pound.
Remove roast when thermometer reaches 140°.
Let stand 15 minutes for medium rare, 155° for medium done.
Carve roast into slices.
Serve with sauce.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Place cinnamon graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix instant pudding with milk and Cool Whip.
Make layers with crackers and mix, spreading evenly.
Place blueberry mix on top and spread to cover. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes; beat until smooth.
Add margarine and eggs and beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients; add milk and beat until smooth.
Stir in half of pecans.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm on top.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining pecans and marshmallows on top.
Brown quickly under broiler.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Pour this mixture into crust.
Sprinkle some of the crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: smothered chicken breast
directions: Season chicken breast, bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes until done.
Place in a casserole dish in single layer.
Brush with honey mustard.
Place 1 tablespoon sliced mushrooms, 1 slice bacon, and 1/4
cup grated cheese on each chicken breast.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes until cheese is completely melted.
Serve hot.

title: coffee cake
directions: Spray a large Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of the pan.
Place frozen dough balls evenly on top of pecans. Sprinkle pudding mix evenly over dough balls.
In a small pan, melt butter and add 1 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and do not boil.
Pour this over dough balls.
(Refrigerate 12 hours or more, optional.)
Bring out of refrigerator about 4 hours before cooking to allow dough to rise.
After it rises, cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown. You may need to lower rack and place foil or cookie sheet under it to catch drips.
When done, invert onto plate at once.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, grapes and walnuts.
Turn fruit mixture into a romaine-lined salad bowl; chill.
Combine mayo, sugar and lemon juice.
Whip cream until soft peaks form; fold into mayo mixture.
Spoon the dressing over the chilled apple mixture. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
To serve, fold dressing into fruit mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coon balls
directions: Note:
Sausage needs to be room temperature.

title: fried squash
directions: Cook the squash in water until done and drain.
Add the onions, milk, salt and pepper to taste and the flour.
Pour in hot greased pan and fry until brown, stirring frequently.

title: creamy herb dip
directions: Combine parsley, dill, Ricotta, yogurt, salt and lemon juice in food processor.
Whirl until smooth, scraping down side of bowl as needed.
Serve immediately or refrigerate, covered, for up to 2 days.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pepper crab soup
directions: Boil pepper and crab in water about 10 minutes; add cheese and simmer to melt.
Add evaporated milk; do not boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Saute in small amount of Crisco until done.
Pour off fat.
Set meat balls aside.

title: lollipops
directions: Mix sugar, water and corn syrup over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 300°.
Remove from heat, add food color of your choice and pour on aluminum foil in desired sizes. Place sticks into lollipops and allow to cool.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: favorite cabbage casserole
directions: Put dried onion flakes in bottom of microwave dish and the water.
Cook 100% power for 10 minutes.
Let stand with cover on for 5 minutes.
Remove cover and add ground turkey or veal, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Microwave at full power for additional 4 minutes.

title: drop-baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in shortening and quickly stir in milk.
Add more little by little to make soft dough.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: coffee punch
directions: In punch bowl, place chilled coffee.
Scoop ice cream or cut into squares and add to coffee.
Add whipped cream just before serving.
Makes approximately 60 cups.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
(Add water if necessary.)
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan or 10-inch heavy skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bread is golden brown and tests done. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cream of tartar into bowl or onto waxed paper.
Set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar in large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Add flour mixture in 4 parts, beating well after each addition.
Shape dough into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Do not flatten! Bake for 12 minutes or until lightly golden around edges.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli tops into bowl with the chopped red onions and grated Cheddar cheese.
Add the fried and crumbled bacon.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie baked in crust
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cornstarch until well blended.
Add cocoa and eggs.
Mix milk, water and vanilla; add to mixture.
The secret to this pie is to mix ingredients well.
Bake in a 350° oven until set, about 45 to 50 minutes.
(Put meringue on 5 minutes before through cooking.)

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Mix rest of ingredients in large cooking pot, add the hamburger and cook on low to medium for 1 hour.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook pie shell 3 minutes at 350°.
Take out and pierce with fork; bake 5 minutes more.
Cool.
Add 3/4 cup cheese on shell; add sausage mix and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° until done, 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put syrup in first; don't need to mix.
Microwave sugar and syrup on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Microwave on High, 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Add baking soda and stir.
Pour out onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In a large saucepan, combine beans and water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans.
In the same pan, combine beans, 4 cups fresh water, pork, celery, onion, thyme, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Remove meat.
When cool enough to handle, cut meat off bones and coarsely chop.
Discard bones and bay leaf.
Slightly mash beans in saucepan.
Return the meat to saucepan.
Heat through.
Makes 4 main-dish servings.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients and fry.
Drain the grease.
Make your favorite baking powder dough. Roll out about 1/4-inch thick in rectangular or square shape. Spread hamburger mixture over all. Roll up like jelly roll. Slice in 1-inch slices.
Put on greased pan and bake at 375° until crust is light brown. Serve with mushroom gravy.
I usually open a can of mushroom soup and use it as gravy.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Crust:
Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 6 tablespoons butter.
Press in pie plate.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
As they "melt" spread over crust.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until fairly stiff but not dry. Add brown sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time. Continue beating. Add pecans.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon on well greased cookie sheet. Will not spread. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes; cool. Store in cookie tin.

title: easy italian vegetable dish
directions: Slice zucchini and line bottom of Corningware dish.
Slice tomatoes and layer on top of zucchini.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese (or any cheese you want) on top. Repeat layers again (2 of each should do it).
Microwave for several minutes until hot and serve (time depends on your wattage).
You can also add onions, ham, etc.

title: pineapple fruit cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix. Pour in tube pan and bake at 375° until done.
Remove and cool.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except meat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cooked meat; heat thoroughly.
Spoon into buns.
Serve at once. Delicious!

title: puff pastry christmas wreaths
directions: Generously grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine completely thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin; set aside.
(No need to sift flour; measure by lightly spooning into cup and leveling off.)
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows in prepared pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over marshmallows in prepared pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool with ice crem or whipped cream.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream well shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix sour milk (add 1 tablespoon vinegar to milk in measuring cup), boiling water and vanilla.
Add cocoa, soda, flour, baking powder and salt alternately to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Lightly cook and drain zucchini.
Mix stuffing with butter. Mix all ingredients with 1/2 stuffing mixture.
Put in casserole and top with balance of stuffing.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: frozie rosie
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon.
Beat about 10 minutes until mixture holds peaks.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put 2/3 crumb mixture on bottom of pan; reserve rest for top.
Freeze until ready to eat.
Let thaw enough to cut before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan and cook until slightly brown.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and cool whip.
Spread over the cookie crust.

title: tuna stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender; drain.
Flake tuna.
Cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Add tuna, 1 1/2 cups herbed stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Stir in zucchini.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and toss with remaining cubes.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: cheese wine log
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until nearly smooth.
Gradually beat in wine.
Add onion and horseradish.
Chill mixture about 1 hour. Shape into 2 logs, each about 6 inches long.
Roll each in half of the beef.

title: french bread
directions: Mix boiling water, butter and sugar together.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients together and stir in 6 or 6 1/2 cups flour.
May be lumpy.
Stir every 10 minutes 5 times.
Divide dough in half; roll like jelly roll. Pinch together.
Cut 3 small slashes on top.
Let rise for about an hour.
Sprinkle cornmeal in greased pans and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: potato and pork chop casserole
directions: Mix everything except pork
chops.
Place in casserole dish. Brown pork chops and place on top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: refrigerated pickles
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients. Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Put into jars and store in refrigerator. Best flavor if you let stand 2 to 3 days.
May add more cucumbers and onion rings when needed.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add beans, seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased casserole (1 or 1 1/2-quart).
Top with cornbread batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream sugar with margarine.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla, flour and soda.
Mix and chill.
Roll between wax paper and put on pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: If you're using frozen hash brown potatoes, press them between paper towels to remove moisture.
Press hash browns onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate to form a crust.
Drizzle melted margarine over crust.
Preheat oven at 425°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: spanish cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift and measure flour, add baking powder, cinnamon and salt and sift three or four times.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients and beat well.
Fold in beaten egg whites, pour in a baking pan and bake for twenty minutes in a moderate oven.
Let cool and spread with brown sugar frosting.

title: layered salad
directions: Alternate layers of lettuce, celery, pepper, onion and green peas twice.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese, bacon and eggs over mayonnaise.
Seal tightly and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix everything together for 4 minutes with electric blender. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 2 greased bread pans lined with wax paper, or can be baked in Bundt pan.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add water and stir well.
Add pineapple and orange juice.
Stir well and add ginger ale.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 gallons.
Change color of punch by the flavor of the Kool-Aid.

title: simple lemon icebox pie
directions: Thaw Cool Whip in refrigerator overnight.
Do not thaw at room temperature as it will adversely affect pie.
Mix thawed Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add lemon juice to preferred tartness.
Mixture will get very thick as lemon juice is stirred in.
Pour into crust and chill for several hours before serving.

title: glazed carrots with bacon and onion
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water to cover in a large saucepan 15 minutes or until carrots are tender. Drain. Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp. Remove bacon and drain on paper towels, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon. set aside. Saut onion in reserved drippings over medium-high heat 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in brown sugar, pepper and carrots. Cook, stirring often, 5 minutes or until carrots are glazed and thoroughly heated. Transfer carrots to a serving dish and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: hazelnut half moon cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts with wooden spoon.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out to approximately 1/2-inch.
Cut into cubes approximately 1-inch square.
Shape into small crescents by first making a ball in hands, then rolling into long shapes, placing on cookie sheet and turning ends into half moon form.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack.
Sprinkle with sugar just before serving.

title: italian chicken and spaghetti(microwave)
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Rinse and drain.
Place on microwave-safe serving platter.
Place each chicken breast between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound with flat side of meat mallet or rolling pin until 1/4-inch thickness.
Top each chicken breast with 1 tablespoon each Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni. Tuck in sides of chicken and roll up with filling sealed inside. Combine bread crumb mixture.
Place in 8-inch square microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with paper towel.

title: 7 day sweet chunk pickle
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water.
Let stand overnight in cool place.
Drain.
Repeat 3 mornings.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Mix well.
Layer mixture in a large bowl with sliced bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: brown rice
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350°
until rice is done and is brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Place butter in 4-cup glass bowl.
Microwave on High 35 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper to form smooth paste.
Gradually whisk in milk until smoothly blended. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until boiling and thickened, stirring every two minutes to ensure smoothness.
Stir in cheese (make sure sauce is completely thickened first).
Stir until melted.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: tina's omelet casserole
directions: Sprinkle meat of your choice, cheese and onion in 10-inch quiche pan (greased).
Beat other ingredients until smooth and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Can prepare the night before.
Great for overnight guests!

title: no fail easy fudge
directions: Combine and blend together all ingredients except sugar.
Then stir in confectioner's sugar to desired consistency.
Refrigerate in buttered pan.
Pan size according to desired thickness.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter, vanilla and brandy in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle first with raisins, then 2/3 cup of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.
Garnish with remaining coconut.

title: custard pie
directions: Refrigerate pie crust while preparing filling.
Add sugar, salt, almond flavoring and vanilla to the eggs, stirring constantly.
Slowly pour in the milk. Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between side and center comes out clean.
Cool.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry with onion.
Do not drain. Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, covered, then 1/2 hour, uncovered.
You may leave in oven longer if soupy.

title: blueberries and cream pie
directions: To prepared blueberry pie filling, in a large saucepan, combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt, lime peel and juice; add 1 1/2 cups blueberries.
Cook mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and blueberries are softened, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining berries.
Let mixture cool to room temperature and chill 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour on cabbage.
Mix and put in fridge.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients but shrimp.
Chop shrimp finely and add to rest of mixture.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: frog leg pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip and milk; beat until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Spread cherries on top.
Chill overnight.

title: french quarter crepes
directions: Sift together first
three ingredients.
Beat eggs until very light.
Stir in milk, half and half and dry ingredients.
Add brandy and beat until smooth.
Preheat a lightly greased crepe or omelet pan or skillet.
Pour in 2 to 3 tablespoons of batter all at once.
Tilt pan quickly and rotate to distribute batter evenly over surface.
Cook the crepe quickly on both sides.
Remove crepe from pan and brush lightly with melted butter.
Repeat until all batter is used.
Keep warm.
Crepes are time consuming to make.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones; saving broth.
Pour rice into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pour 1 cup chicken broth over rice. Place chicken pieces over rice.
Blend the two soups with one cup milk and pour over chicken and rice.
Melt margarine and mix with remaining one-quarter cup chicken broth.
Pour over stuffing mix and blend well.
Place over chicken ingredients in casserole. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Follow directions on box for cake, substituting pineapple juice (strain crushed pineapple) and add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until done. Cut cake in two layers (horizontally). Blend cream cheese (room temperature), instant vanilla pudding and milk.
Fold in crushed pineapple and mix well.
Place half the pineapple mixture in between layers and remainder on top. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and chopped walnuts. Refrigerate until needed. Cake also freezes well.

title: peanut butter pancakes
directions: In a blender, mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Cook pancakes until tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.
Flip and cook other side.
Makes approximately 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a small saucepan add oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
Cream together eggs, sugar and sour cream or buttermilk in a large mixing bowl.
Add the cocoa-oleo mixture. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to the 2 mixtures and fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in an 11 x 17-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Season tomatoes with salt, onion and pepper.
Fill baking dish with crumbs and tomatoes, in alternate layers, with crumbs on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for half hour.
May sprinkle cheese on top.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in margarine, eggs and cheese. Form crust in greased 10-inch pie pan.
Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and salt.
Spread Ricotta on spaghetti.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix soup, broth and green chilies; set aside.
Mix chicken and onions together.
Put 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on a tortilla and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up tortilla and place in a greased cake pan.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook noodles in chicken broth; add onion, bell pepper and garlic to a small amount of broth.
Cook until tender; add to noodles along with cheese, mushroom soup, milk, salt, pepper and oregano.
Put cheese slices on top and cook until hot through in oven or microwave.

title: to corn meat
directions: *If beef, use brisket or eye of round.

title: black and white cheesecake bites
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
To make crust, melt chips and butter in a medium pan over very low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in crumbs.
Remove 1/4 cup for later use.
Press remaining mixture evenly in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.

title: broccoli  casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 10 x
13-inch pan.
Mix soup and milk; pour over broccoli.
Place chestnuts on top of broccoli.
Cover with grated cheese.
Place onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, milk, corn flakes, salt, pepper, catsup and bell pepper.
Form into patties. Roll in flour.
Brown in oil. Place in baking pan. Cover with mushroom soup, 1/2 can water and Kitchen Bouquet browning and seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: friendship soup
directions: Wash beans; cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans. Add 2 quarts water, ham hock, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes or longer, stirring occasionally. Remove ham hock from soup.
Chop meat up and return to soup. Makes approximately 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate crack cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in a large double boiler or a mixing bowl over hot water.
Remove from water and blend in oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Chill soft dough for several hours or overnight.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Beat together the butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Save 1 1/2 cups of mixture. Spread 1 can cherry pie filling over this real thin.
Leave 1/2-inch from each side.
Spread rest of flour mixture thin over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing or glaze.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch cake pan.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add onion and saute over medium heat 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer over very low heat 20 minutes.
Add chicken, pepper, tomato, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer over low heat 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve sour cream separately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar.
Beat until well blended; add lemon juice and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: lo-cal lemon cheesecake
directions: Soften gelatin in water; add lemon juice and heat to dissolve gelatin.
Cool slightly; beat in egg yolks, pureed cottage cheese and Neufchatel cheese and Equal.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into cheese mixture.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers, side by side.
Pour cheese mixture over crackers; chill overnight until firm.

title: deer jerky
directions: Soak meat in this mixture 2 to 3 hours.
Put on paper towels to blot.
Put meat over racks in oven.
Turn oven as low as it will go.
Cook 8 to 9 hours with door ajar.
Air dry 8 hours. Store in jars or Ziploc bags.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water until cooked through. Once cooked, cut into small pieces. Mix sour cream and soup in baking pan. Add chicken to mix and stir thoroughly. Crumble Ritz crackers over top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken into a greased baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup, and berries in a bowl and then pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees, uncovered for 50-60 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of warm water.
Combine milk and cold water and heat until almost boiling.
Pour hot liquid over butter, honey, raisins and salt in a large bowl and stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast mixture and oats. Beat in 2 cups of the flour until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining flour and stir to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until elastic, about 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl.
Turn to coat and let stand, covered, until doubled in size.
Punch dough down and shape to form 2 loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until nearly doubled.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bread sounds hollow when tapped.
Cool on racks.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Put fruit in baking pan.
Mix sugar with cake mix.
(Do not make cake!)
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: red pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers 1/2-inch thick.
Soak 24 hours in lime to 2 gallons water.
Rinse lime off and soak 2 hours in cold water, then drain.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, red food coloring and alum.
Put in enough water to cover pickles and simmer for 1 hour, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and pour over pickles and let stand overnight.
Heat for 3 days and on the third day, put into jars and seal.

title: deviled ham cheese log
directions: Combine deviled ham, pecans, cream cheese, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce in bowl; mix well.
Shape into roll.
Chill until firm.
Shape into log on waxed paper sprinkled generously with paprika.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
Serve on crackers or party rye.

title: potatoes and dumplings
directions: Peel potatoes and dice them.
Chop onions small and fry them in oil.
Add salt, paprika and diced potatoes.
Cook for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and strain; add eggs, slightly beaten.
Add soup, milk, onion and salt, then add 1/2 cup of cooked rice.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Using refrigerated butterflake rolls, peel dough into 36 discs.
Spread each with crabmeat mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until dough discs have cooked and topping is bubbly.
Makes 36.

title: capelli d'angelo with hazelnut butter and crisp asparagus(prep: 20 minutes, cook: 10 minutes, serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast hazelnuts in a baking pan until lightly browned and skins begin to crack, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a kitchen towel and rub briskly with the towel to loosen sides.
Select 8 hazelnuts; coarsely chop and set aside for garnish.
Grind the remaining nuts in a food processor or Mouli grater.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; set aside. Combine all ingredients, except mini chips and walnuts, in a large mixing bowl; blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place meat on a piece of aluminum foil large enough to wrap around the meat. Cover both sides of the meat with liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce and tenderizer. Sprinkle seasonings on both sides of meat. Seal foil around meat.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Base:
Mix gelatin, pineapple (drain and save juice), 7-Up, 2 cups boiling water and sliced bananas.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and let chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook until tender enough to mash.
Mash.
Add cream cheese, half and half, margarine, garlic powder, seasoning salt, pepper and salt.
Mix until it is the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes or so.
Will serve 10.

title: microwave chocolate fudge(cooking time:  10 minutes)
directions: Lightly butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar, butter and milk in a 3-quart glass bowl.
Cook on High for 9 to 10 minutes, or until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Stir in chocolate morsels and Marshmallow Creme until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: cajun chow mein
directions: Crumble and brown meat in skillet until all pinkness is gone. Drain excess grease.
Combine meat and all other ingredients. (Add all liquids including juices from Chinese vegetables, mushrooms, etc.)
In large casserole dish or a 13 x 9-inch pan, cover and bake in 400° oven for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Combine margarine, garlic salt and hot sauce and let simmer while cooking wings.
Deep fry wings and drain.
Coat wings with sauce thoroughly.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes; preheat oven.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dressing.

title: wanda's potato soup
directions: Cook together potatoes, onion, carrot, celery and chicken flavor cubes.
Cook vegetables until tender; save liquid.
Make white sauce with butter and flour, slowly adding hot milk and vegetable liquid until creamy.
Add leftover mashed potatoes, if you have any.
Add any vegetables and seasonings.

title: apple crow's nest
directions: Arrange apples in greased pie tin and dot with butter. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Put flour, baking powder, salt and 1/4 cup sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough milk gradually to make a soft dough. Spread over apples.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until apples are tender, about 25 minutes.
Turn out upside down.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir well.
In a shaker, place egg and dry mixture, then milk.
Shake well.
Using a funnel, place finger over bottom of funnel and fill.
Remove finger; pour in circular pattern into hot grease (about 375°).
Cook to a light golden brown.
Cover by sprinkling on powdered sugar, syrup or cinnamon and sugar.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: In crock-pot, rinse beans and cover with 6 cups water (water should be 1 to 2-inches above ingredients at all times).
Cook overnight (6 hours) on high.
Add all other ingredients and stewed tomatoes; cook on high 1 to 2 more hours, until vegetables are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: festive strawberry punch
directions: Mix in order given.
Will serve 30 to 40.

title: country steak and gravy
directions: Cut round steak into pieces.
Batter in flour, salt, and pepper.
Have oil hot in skillet.
Brown the meat.
Remove to crockpot.
Make gravy in skillet and pour over steak.
Have meat covered.
Start on high and then reduce heat.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Set aside to use later.
Melt butter in a saucepan large enough for cooking potatoes.
Add potatoes, onion, water, salt, bay leaf, paprika and ground red pepper. Cover and cook over moderate heat until potatoes are tender, but not soft.
Add vinegar and bring to boiling point.
Boil 1 minute. Add sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: huntington chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken (save broth to boil noodles with). After noodles are boiled, steam juices and mix broth, soups and cheese with chicken and noodles.

title: red chile(asado)
directions: Brown meat well.
Boil chile pods.
Blend well in blender.
Add garlic, bay leaves and 2 teaspoons cuminos to chile in blender. Fry meat with 1 teaspoon cuminos.
Add white flour; brown until tender.
Add chile, then oregano and salt.
Boil and simmer for 30 minutes, until well done.

title: german potato salad with kielbasa
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until brown.
Add onions and flour; cook until bubbly.
Add next 6 ingredients; bring to boil. Add kielbasa.
Cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in potatoes and parsley gently, coating potatoes with sauce.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Serve immediately.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and milk, adding flour, salt and vanilla. Pour into baking dish over fruit.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°. Ready to serve.

title: snow pea stir-fry
directions: Lightly coat nonstick skillet or wok with cooking spray.
Add snow peas, carrots, mushrooms and onions.
Stir-fry on medium heat until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add soy sauce and cooked pasta.
Toss together and heat 1 to 2 minutes until hot.
Serves 4.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix together milk and chocolate.
Melt over low heat.
Turn heat off.
Butter pan.
Add nuts and vanilla to chocolate mixture. Pour into buttered pan. Put in refrigerator until cooled.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix together and heat slowly until hot.
Serve in coffee cups or mugs.

title: venison roast baked in browning bag
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place roast on cutting board and season as desired with Tony Chachere seasoning.
Cut garlic and poke holes in roast.
Place garlic in holes.
Prepare bag by shaking 2 tablespoons flour in bag.
Place roast and onion soup in bag.
Tie and poke holes in top.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: jim's famous meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, parsley, eggs, minced onion, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder and ketchup.
Make 50 to 60 meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet close together.
Cook cranberry sauce over medium heat until melted.
Spoon over each meatball, using all the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Even better if made a day ahead and reheated.

title: sauteed asparagus
directions: Cut off tips of asparagus.
Cut tender part of the stalk to 2 1/2 to 3-inch pieces.
Halve or quarter if necessary.
Saute asparagus in olive oil.
Add garlic salt to your taste.
When tender, it's done.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Stir just enough to blend eggs and ingredients together.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir just to blend.
Do not overbeat.
Add margarine and butter extract; stir quickly.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes or until center of custard is set. Allow to cool before cutting.
Bake a day ahead if possible.

title: pepper roast and gravy
directions: Rub roast with pepper and cardamom to cover.
Press in with heel of hand.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Mix together the tomato paste, paprika and garlic powder.
Gradually add soy sauce and vinegar.
Pour over roast and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Remove roast from marinade and wrap in foil.
Reserve marinade for gravy. Cook in shallow pan at 300° for 2 hours.
Open foil and ladle off drippings.
Brown, uncovered, at 350°.
While meat is browning, strain and defat pan drippings.
Top 1 cup of drippings, add 1 cup of water and bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup reserved marinade. Thicken with flour mixed with remaining water, if desired.
Slice roast thinly and diagonally and serve with gravy.
Serves 12.

title: shower cake
directions: Use a jelly roll pan and bake as directed on box and add oil. Mix pudding as directed in a large bowl.
Fold in cream cheese. Beat.
Drain pineapple; fold into pudding mixture.
Put on top of cooled cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, adding 3 tablespoons creme de menthe to batter.
Cool.
Frost with fudge frosting.
Add 5 tablespoons creme de menthe liqueur to Cool Whip.
Spread over frosting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cracker crumbs and oleo. Bake in greased casserole dish at 350°.
Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: surprise macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain, rinse in cold water.
Drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Soak 1/2 to
cup dry soy beans in cold water overnight. Rinse
and
drain.
Blend all except spinach.
Pour in bowl and stir
in spinach.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Keep sides of crust low to prevent burning.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan over medium heat.

Add cocoa. Heat until mixture begins to boil. Stirring constantly until smooth. Pour into small mixer bowl. Cool completely. Add powdered sugar alternating with milk. Beat to spreading consistency. Blend in vanilla.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save 1 cup liquid from can of pineapple.
Drain all the cans of fruit.
Add package of vanilla pudding mix to the reserved cup of pineapple juice; stir until smooth.
Put all drained and fresh fruit in a large bowl.
Spread vanilla pudding mixture on top of fruit; stir until mixed well.

title: oatmeal cookie spread
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar with baking soda, baking powder and salt, then add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread onto cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Cut into any size pieces.

title: basic zabaglione
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar (slowly).
Add slowly the liquor. Beat until it thickens enough to hold a slight peak when whip is withdrawn.
Depends on utensil used (could take up to 5 minutes). Makes enough to fill a birthday torte or 1 dozen creme puffs.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip.
Layer as follows:
Vanilla wafers, 1/2 of bananas and 1/2 of pudding.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 45 minutes at 350° or 7 minutes in microwave. Turn dish around and bake 5 minutes more.

title: greek chicken
directions: In large roasting pan, arrange cut up chicken (remove chicken skin).
Also in pan, add diced carrots and potatoes.

title: susan dillard's "sloppy joes"
directions: Brown onion in small amount of oil.
Add beef and brown. Drain, then add all other ingredients and simmer for about 30 minutes over medium heat.
Delicious served on bun with dill pickle slices.

title: barbecue chicken pizza
directions: Combine chicken and barbecue sauce.
Place pizza crust on a baking sheet.
Spread chicken mixture over pizza crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: zucchini or eggplant lasagna
directions: Cook zucchini or eggplant until tender-crisp; drain.
Cook beef and garlic until beef is brown.
Stir in sauce and herbs. Mix cottage cheese, egg and parsley.
Put 1/2 of zucchini or eggplant in a greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Spread with half of the cottage cheese mixture, then with half beef mixture and half Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, except for Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella; bake about 3 minutes, until cheese is melted.
(Can use Ricotta cheese instead of cottage.)

title: jalapeno quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Spray a 9 x 11-inch baking dish with Pam
or grease with butter.
Chop peppers and spread in bottom of
dish.
Spread
bacon over the peppers and sprinkle cheese over the
bacon.
Beat
eggs
until fluffy and pour over top
of
the
cheese.
Bake
at
for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove
from oven, cut into squares and serve upside down while hot.

title: squash relish vegetables
directions: Mix and let sit for 1 hour.
Then drain in a colander.

title: jogging in jug
directions: Use regular juice, not concentrate. Mix together and take 2 ounces every day. Keep refrigerated.

title: fran's brisket
directions: You will need a large sheet double strength foil.

title: marinade for venison or elk
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together well.
Add meat and stir to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 10 to 12 hours. Drain well before cooking as desired.

title: tomato paste sauce
directions: Brown garlic in hot oil.
Add tomato paste, water and herbs. Simmer on low heat for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally. If too thick, add a little water.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Mix together.
Beat with mixer while cooking, about 3 minutes, until light fluffy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Good with crushed pineapple for layer cake.

title: ham caribbean
directions: Slice ham at 1-inch intervals. Place on rack in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook 3 minutes, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
(For fudge candy, cook for 4 minutes.)
When cool, beat and spread on cake.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water; set aside.
Dredge meat in flour and seasonings.
Brown meat in 1/4 cup of shortening.
Add onion and saute in remaining shortening.
Add onion, mushrooms and bouillon to meat; mix thoroughly.
Cover and bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in sour cream.
Serve on buttered noodles or rice.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box and bake in an
oblong pan. When cake is done, poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Let it sit and soak for a short time.
Pour cream of coconut over top.
Let cool, then mix coconut with Cool Whip and spread over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian cheese balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls.
Lightly brown in oiled frypan, only enough to set balls. Put in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, reserving cheese.
Pour sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Brown skinned chicken in oleo or butter.
Blend wine, soup and seasonings.
Add chestnuts.
Place chicken and mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, cream and butter together and bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Set off stove and stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour in pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: calico veggies
directions: Put potatoes in a skillet with a little water. Cook until half done.
Add squash and okra.
Add extra water, if needed. Season to taste with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
When all veggies are tender, it is ready.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Butter a 10-inch pie plate.
Crumble bacon into pan and strew cheese and onion evenly over bacon.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan and bake 50 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into pie shaped serving pieces.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Melt chocolate bars over double boiler.
Combine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mocha frosty
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add coffee granules, stirring to dissolve.
Chill.
Combine chocolate mixture, milk and ice cream in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Top each serving with a dollop of whipped topping.
Serve immediately. Yields 5 cups.

title: pork adobo
directions: Cut pork in 1/2 to 1-inch cubes.
Boil in water for about 10 minutes.
Drain water.
Add soy sauce and vinegar to meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Simmer on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot over rice or noodles.
Can use chicken pieces instead of pork if you want.

title: stromboli(pizza bread)
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in sauce. Roll out crescent rolls in 11 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread half of the meat mixture on the rectangle.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Seal well.
Repeat with 2nd crescent roll package.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 rolls.
Slice to serve as a main course or appetizer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, boil squash and onion together until tender.
Drain well.
In a large bowl, mix squash, egg, margarine, sugar, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 cracker crumbs, soup and seasonings. Mix well.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese and crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef casserole
directions: Melt shortening and add beef, onion and pepper.
Brown slightly.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Add macaroni, tomatoes, ketchup, salt and pepper to browned mixture. Mix and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with slices of cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a heavy pan over low heat.
Pour in peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields 40 servings.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain the pineapple and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix sugar, cheese and flour and spread over pineapple. Crush the crackers over top of cheese mixture. Pour melted margarine over crackers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and eggs; add your boiling water with soda and flour.
Drop in greased cookie sheet with spoon and bake.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate with 1 1/2 cups water and butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir into boiling chocolate mixture; add vanilla.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Set aside and prepare dumplings.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onion in oil until brown.
Add rice and saute.
Mix in eggs, soy sauce and salt.
At this point, 1 1/2 cups crumbled cooked bacon, ham or shrimp may be added.
This may be made in advance and reheated in a small amount of oil after the addition of the eggs.

title: stone soup(without the stones)
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil, then simmer 1/2 hour. Add rice, peas and beans; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add carrots, potatoes and cabbage.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato soup and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken until done.
Mix the cream of celery and cream of chicken soup with 1 can of water.
Place chunks of chicken in casserole dish. Add soup and water mixture. Add chicken broth with herb stuffing mix.
Put on top of soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and chopped pecans.
Press into pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: simmered squash
directions: Put oil in large skillet with lid; layer onion, potatoes and squash (lightly salt and pepper each layer) in skillet.
Cover with lid and simmer on stove top for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: date bars
directions: Beat room temperature egg whites in a bowl that is set in warm water.
Beat until very stiff.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Pour and stir the mixture into the egg whites.
Add, by handful, the pecans and dates, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
