Put the mixture into a "well" greased 10 x 16-inch pan.
The mixture is very thick, so set 2 table knives in a glass of hot water and alternate them to spread the batter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Remove from oven and cut immediately into strips.
Roll them in powdered sugar.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: fluffy sunshine cake
directions: Combine shortening, orange peel and lemon peel.
Mix well. Add sugar gradually. Cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with lemon juice and milk, a small amount at a time. Beat after each addition until smooth.
Bake in 2 paper lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans in moderate oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until done. Cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer lettuce, chopped hard-boiled eggs, celery, green peppers, onion, carrots, uncooked frozen peas, Miracle Whip with sugar, bacon bits and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup of sugar; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: Melt or microwave for 1 minute and 25 seconds on Defrost the chips and syrup.
Add milk; microwave 30 seconds on regular heat until blended.
Add vanilla.
Serve over ice cream.

title: stuffed artichoke
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese and garlic very well with a fork. Add olive oil and mix (it should be moist).
Cut top and bottom from artichoke; turn upside down and mash slightly to open leaves. Fill each leaf by pulling leaf down some and stuff.
Start at bottom and work way to top.
Steam in covered pot in a little water (enough water so that it comes up to the stem, but not up to the artichoke).
Steam for 45 minutes or longer.
Add water as necessary.
Is done when leaf pulls off easily.

title: rice, corn and cheese casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except paprika and mix well.
Pour ingredients into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Mix with beaten egg.
Combine all seasonings and combine with bread and egg.
Blend in crabmeat. Shape into 8 cakes.
Fry in small amount of hot oil.

title: hot punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients to the water and sugar.
Let mixture simmer.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Discard water.
Dice potatoes (skin on), celery, carrots and onion.
Put in 6-quart pot.
Add ham. Cover with water.
Simmer 5 hours.
Remove ham.
Discard fat and bone.
Cut ham into bite-size.
Return to soup.
If soup is too thin, cook longer; if too thick, add water.
Serve with toasted bagels.

title: fruit ice
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar (or less) and 1 cup water; cool.
Mix with fruit.
Freeze until ice crystals form.
Mix again and refreeze.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine, fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add cornbread mix to egg mixture.
Add onion and green pepper.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread sour cream over cornbread mixture and top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can put aluminum foil over top until last few minutes to let topping brown.

title: old settler baked beans
directions: Brown bacon with onion.
Add hamburg and continue browning. Put browned meat in casserole dish and add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat after each addition until creamy.
Spoon into graham cracker pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let pies set for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all together well except nuts.
Add nuts last.
Makes 1 pie.
Bake in pie crust at 375°.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan; add cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Mix and spread over baked cake and return to oven until lightly browned.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle on 1/2 sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar, oats and flour.
Mix together and spread on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sammie's chocolate lush
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with hands and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool crust.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix apples and nuts.
Sift flour with soda, salt and sugar. Add apples, nuts, egg, butter and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with hot lemon or pineapple sauce.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: easy baked halibut
directions: Grease 8 x 8 inch baking dish.
Cover with onions then Miracle Whip.
Place fillets on top.
Cover with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes or till cheese is melted.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place refried beans in bowls.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and Ranch mix.
Place on beans.
Add cheese and onions. (Purple onions will make a pretty dish.)

title: peanut butter cookies *
directions: Blend peanut butter and butter.
Cream mixture with sugars and salt thoroughly.
Beat egg and extract into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and soda.
Gradually blend into creamed ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
With floured fork, make a crisscross design to flatten cookies.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 18 to 20 minutes or until light brown around edges. Store in airtight container.
Yield: 3 dozen large cookies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place meat in a 2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry soup mix over top.
Spoon mushroom soup over this, then add Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat, stirring constantly (a double boiler is best).
Mix noodles and peanuts into pan, coating evenly.
Spoon mixture onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan.
Fry onions until golden.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; pour in pre-greased pan and bake as directed on cornbread package.

title: orange juice pie
directions: Bring the 2 juices to boil and add 1/2 pound marshmallows. Stir until dissolved.
Let cool (start to jell) and whip 1 cup cream.
Mix together.
Make crust with wafers and butter.
Pour mixture into vanilla wafer crust.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies.
Cut in 1/2-inch squares.
Put the following items in a large bowl:
half the brownies, half the chocolate mousse, half the Cool Whip, half the pecans and half the Heath bars.
Repeat.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add gelatin mixture, blending thoroughly.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together all other ingredients except Cheddar cheese and pour into buttered pan. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.
(Good with black-eyed peas.)

title: italian style chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Sift 1 teaspoon salt and flour to coat chicken.
Saute chicken in oil until brown.
Place in covered dish to keep warm.

title: sand cookies
directions: Mix with hands.
Divide dough into 4 rolls.
Refrigerate. Slice thinly and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put into greased dish (grease with butter).
Bake at 300° to 400° until pudding sets or is dry on top.

title: turkey chili
directions: Combine chili powder, cayenne, oregano, basil, red pepper, cumin and paprika.
Add to ground turkey and mix well.
Combine turkey mixture with onion.
Add Worcestershire sauce and wine. Cover and cook over medium heat 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Add garlic, tomato paste and catsup and mix well.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with chopped onion.

title: peanut butter, chocolate, oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: red bean dip
directions: Process the ingredients in a blender.
Heat and serve with low-fat crackers.
Makes 1 cup.

title: poured crust pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease and flour a 12 to 14-inch pizza pan.
Combine flour, salt, Italian seasoning, pepper, eggs and milk; blend until smooth.
Pour batter into pan, tilting to cover. Sprinkle with meat mixture (if using uncooked meat, brown and drain), onion and mushrooms.
Bake on low rack for 25 to 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Fry butter, onions and peppers until brown.
Then combine butter, onions and peppers with remaining ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook on low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: english drop cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: delhi tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Serve with Curry Dressing.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature. Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream oleo and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time and combine banana and buttermilk in small cup.
In a small bowl, mix flour, soda, banana pudding and salt.
Add flour alternately with banana mix to egg mix.
Fold in chopped cherries.
Pour into an ungreased loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: saucy smoked sausage
directions: Saute sausage (cut up in bite-size pieces) in butter.
Stir in green pepper, onion and garlic and saute further.
Stir in tomato sauce and simmer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Pour
into unbaked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes at 275°; turn up to 300° and bake 55 minutes or until done.

title: carrot relish
directions: Chop or grind vegetables.
Heat spice, salt, sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Add vegetables and boil gently for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and cover with liquid.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and mix with other ingredients. Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and margarine.
Cook in double boiler until thickens some.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch dish lined with vanilla wafers and alternate layers with wafers.
Refrigerate.
Serve with topping, if preferred.
This is Bob's favorite dessert.

title: nana's holiday jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with water.
Add ice cubes; stir.
Add other ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Put in refrigerator until firm (about 2 hours).
Great for Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions into 1 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Drain salad and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake one hour at 350°.

title: flour and kool-aid clay
directions: Place ingredients in an ovenproof bag; a Ziploc freezer bag works also.
Add 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon salad or cooking oil.
Mix by kneading in bag until consistency of play dough.
(This takes a while.)
Will keep in bag for weeks at room temperature.
The Kool-Aid gives it color and a delicious smell.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Fold in egg whites in last. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together for 20 minutes.
Fold and stir in eggs, one at a time, then flour, lemon and 7-Up.
Bake at 325° for one hour in a Bundt-style cake pan.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Place in covered dish and store in refrigerator.
Pinch off needed amount and knead on floured board.
Cut into biscuits. Do not have to rise. Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: pennsylvania dutch funnel cakes
directions: In medium size bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Gradually beat in milk.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until smooth. In skillet, heat 3/4-inch oil or enough shortening to make 3/4-inch.
Heat until hot enough to fry.
Strain batter into a small pitcher or large measuring cup.
Pour batter into a funnel, holding finger over bottom opening.
Using finger to control batter, start at center of skillet, form a spiral about 6-inches across.
Fry until golden brown.
Remove with a pancake turner. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Repeat process for each funnel cake.

title: almost dairy queen hot chocolate sauce
directions: Cook over moderate heat, until blended, the first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly.
Add the milk and bring to boil, constantly stirring, until thickened.
Remove from heat, adding 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Pour oil into pan; place in a 425° oven to heat for 10 minutes.
Remove pan. Place chicken, skin side down, in hot oil.
Sprinkle lightly with 1/2 the oregano, salt and paprika.
Return pan to oven; bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; sprinkle lightly with remaining oregano, salt and paprika.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Remove from oven and spoon drippings over chicken.
Pour mushrooms with liquid over chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pasta with onions and anchovies(easy sauce to make while pasta cooks)
directions: Cook spaghetti pasta according to package instructions.
While that is cooking, combine garlic and Puritan in small saucepan. Brown garlic in oil.
(Browned garlic will prevent "garlic breath". Uncooked garlic is the culprit!)
Add tomato, basil and oregano just until heated.
When spaghetti is cooked al dente (just slightly undercooked), drain.
Do not rinse.
In large pasta bowl, add oil/garlic mixture and toss thoroughly.
Cracked black pepper should be added by each individual.
Eat immediately.

title: "ruby slippers"
directions: Combine dry cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs.
Blend until creamy, then beat with mixer.
Spoon 1/3 of batter into a 10-inch spring form pan, well greased.
Sprinkle with 1/2 box of jello. Top with 1/3 of batter, then sprinkle rest of jello on top.
Put rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: red punch
directions: Put cold water in bowl.
Add Kool-Aid and stir in sugar.
Then add 1 bottle 7-Up, then juice, then 1 bottle 7-Up.
Add sherbet.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in tight container.
Use 1/2 cup mix to hot water.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Brown sausage (use medium or hot).
Mix onion, pepper and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix with hominy and sausage.
Layer with cheese.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and pumpkin. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in loaf pans or vegetable or coffee cans. Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan or can.
Freezes well.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and work into paste.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in closed container.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; put salmon, egg, onion, parsley, lemon juice, bread, baking soda, salt and pepper in bowl and mix.
Add milk if needed to have a meat loaf consistency.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Serve sliced, with White Sauce.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add mixture of flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Gradually stir in milk and vanilla.
Stir constantly. Scorches easily.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Serve on hot buttered biscuits or pancakes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together and spread over crumbs.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits according to package.
Remove from fire. Add 1 stick of oleo and 1 roll of garlic cheese.
Put eggs in measuring cup.
Beat and fill cup with milk to 1 cup.
Add to grit mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven and cook for 30 more minutes.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Mix ingredients together and then press in pan, bake for 15 minutes at 350 F.

title: baked beans, beans, beans
directions: Mix all beans together in large casserole.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar. Mix well.
Brown onion and bacon. Drain grease.
Add to bean mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar or sugars, then add eggs and pulp. Mix flour, salt and soda along with spices.
Add to liquid ingredients, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine together.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Cook raspberries, sugar, water and cornstarch until thickened.
Cool.
After cooling, pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes. Start timing after mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; beat until blended, then drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
These may be placed in the refrigerator to hasten hardening.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Drain well and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook onions in boiling, salted water until tender; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup milk; cook and stir until bubbly. Reduce heat and blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Place vegetable in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over.
Mix lightly. Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Rub butter into pie crust bottom.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and cook for 35 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Combine ingredients in a large dutch oven; set aside until mixture forms a syrup.
Bring peach mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low and cook uncovered 5 to 10 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk and cook over very low heat until thickened.
Remove and let cool.
Cream sugar, butter and vanilla very rapidly until fluffy.
Add to flour mixture and beat hard. It takes a lot of hard beating until sugar granules are gone. Frost cake.

title: jello pear salad
directions: Drain pears well. Put jello into pear juice.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Let cool.

title: deep fried twinkies
directions: Chill the twinkie by keeping it in the refrigerator.
DO NOT FREEZE.
Mix the flours and baking soda together.
Add milk or beer (beer gives lighter results) until you get a batter with the consistency of thin cream.
Heat the oil until a small piece of bread will brown in a few seconds, but do not allow oil to smoke. Remove the twinkie from refrigerator, coat completely in the batter.
Lower into the hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Can sprinkle fried twinkie with powered sugar, cinnamon or add some fruit toppings.
Kids like theirs topped with chocolate syrup.

title: pickled squash
directions: In a large container, combine squash, onion and peppers. Sprinkle salt over vegetable mixture. Let stand 1 to 1 1/2 hours, drain well. Meanwhile, mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed in saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook for one minute. Remove from heat and pour over vegetables and mix well. Bring back to a rolling boil for about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add pimento. Fill clean jars with hot mixture and seal. Makes about 4 pints. For a brighter yellow color add a little turmeric.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in microwave for 8 minutes, stirring every 3 or 4 minutes until thick.
Pour in cooked pie shell.

title: "i hate to cook stew"
directions: Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook with lid on.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Beat eggs, sugar, shortening, vanilla and milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add egg mixture.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake for 12 minutes. Makes 2 or 3 dozen.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together, form into balls
and place in baking dish.
Mix 1 cup ketchup with 1
cup
water,
pour over meatballs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Brown chicken in nonstick skillet.
Drain off fat.
Toss chicken with 1 teaspoon paprika, then add bouillon cube dissolved in boiling water and onion.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 35 to 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Reduce heat and stir in 1 teaspoon paprika, salt, pepper and yogurt.
Heat well, but do not boil.
Serve garnished with chives.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in crock-pot or oven until hot.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake comes away from sides of pan.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Mix orange juice as directed.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Perk in large party perk coffee pot.

title: bacon and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix 2 cups Miracle Whip (not mayonnaise) with 1/4 cup sugar and spread over the top of layers as you would frosting.
Seal to edges.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Leave salad layered and chill at least 4 hours.
Toss well before serving.

title: low-fat pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan lightly with margarine (do not flour).
In a small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each biscuit in sugar mixture until well coated.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour into tube pan.
After coating each piece of biscuit, drop into tube pan, sprinkling sugar mixture each time.
Add all pieces.
Pour remaining sugar mixture on top. Melt and add last stick of margarine.
Cook in oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Be sure it turns golden brown before removing.
Remove from pan immediately (if allowed to remain in tube pan, it'll stick).
Do not cut pieces off for eating; pinch!

title: crock-pot ravioli casserole
directions: Defrost spinach.
Squeeze dry.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Brown meats and onion in oil until crumbly.
Add tomato sauce, salt and oregano.
Cover. Simmer 30 minutes.
Mix in spinach.
Spoon half the noodles into a buttered crock-pot.
Top with half of meat mixture and half the Parmesan cheese.
Cover with layers of remaining noodles, meat and Parmesan cheese.
Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with Jack cheese and onions.
Cook on high 300° for 1 hour.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Press on bottom of a 9 x 3 x 2-inch cake pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Add 3/4 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar; mix thoroughly.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk with mixer until thick, approximately 2 minutes.
Spread for next layer. Top with remaining Cool Whip, then sprinkle grated Hershey bar shavings on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: minnesota "crab" cakes
directions: Combine sea legs, bread crumbs, onion and parsley in a medium sized bowl.
Stir in milk, egg, Worcestershire and lemon juice. Mix well.
Shape into 8 patties, adding additional bread crumbs, if needed.
Cook patties in 1/4 cup butter for 2 minutes on each side.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil in small saucepan.
Add dry jello; stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add the Sprite; add it slowly, because it will foam up.
Pour into mold or pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: frozen cream soup flavor balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until dough leaves side of bowl and rounds into ball.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Freeze until firm, about one hour.
Freeze and store in plastic covered container and use as flavor and thickening for cream soups.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Season apples with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place in pan.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and egg with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Pour oil over all and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: seafood italian style
directions: Pour olive oil in pan, enough to cover the bottom.
Throw in diced seafood (any type can be used, for example, diced tuna, swordfish, scallops) and cook approximately 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper and white wine.
Simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: baked chicken(good dish for low-fat diet)
directions: Salt chicken and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle flour over top of chicken, then sprinkle remaining spices onto chicken. Bake at
350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covering with aluminum foil the first hour.
Uncover and bake final 15 minutes to allow chicken to brown slightly.

title: reunion casserole
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown beef, sausage and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, green pepper, corn, soup, tomato sauce, salt and noodles.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chewy rocky road bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In small bowl, combine pretzels and butter. Press evenly into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumb mixture. Top with marshmallows, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. Press toppings firmly into sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars. Yields about 36 bars.

title: gnocchis
directions: Mix.
Roll.
Slice.
Roll into rope shapes.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Boil until they bounce up to the top of the water.
Cook a few more minutes.
Serve with spaghetti sauce.
Easier and better than the typical potato-type gnocchi.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Scramble eggs and set aside.
Dice onion and bell pepper.
Mix rice according to package directions on box.
Crumble bacon up and add to rice.
Add eggs, onion and bell pepper.
Mix well.

title: oriental chicken
directions: In a heated wok, saute garlic in peanut oil.
Season chicken strips with salt and pepper.
Add to wok and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots to chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Add soy sauce, sesame oil, oyster sauce and ginger.
Mix well.
Add the remaining vegetables.
Cook for an additional 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and shrimp together until fluffy. Refrigerate until 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with seafood cocktail sauce splashed on top or on the side and crackers.

title: tahitian punch
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together juices and carbonated beverage.
Spoon sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately.
Can add gin, vodka or rum if desired.
May exclude sherbet.

title: apple crescents
directions: First, cover baking sheet with foil.
Roll crescents out and place 1 heaping tablespoon of apple pie filling in center. Sprinkle with a pinch of sugar and a pinch of cinnamon.
Roll crescent up and pinch so it doesn't unroll in oven.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Mix powdered sugar with water and dribble over crescents.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry at 375°. Use waxed paper and grease skillet before putting pancakes in. Do not turn but once. After first mixing of ingredients do not stir the batter again. 1/4 cup batter per pancake = 4 inch pancake.

title: jim's chunky hog lip dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, soup and Jell-O together in a saucepan over low heat until heated and dissolved.
Add the other ingredients and serve warm or cooled.
Don't let the name fool you. It's great.
(Fat-free and sugar-free works well too.)

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toss asparagus with oil, salt and pepper.
Spread on baking sheet, roast 8 - 10 minutes.
Cool. Toss asparagus with baby salad, add vinaigrette - sprinkle with raspberries.

title: omelet for a crowd
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add potatoes.
Fry until golden brown.
Spread in 2 (9 x 13-inch ) pans.
Set aside.
Stir together mushrooms, cheese, egg yolks and salt; set aside.
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.
Fold cheese mixture into egg whites.
Layer meat onto potato layer, then pour egg mixture over. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dilly cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper-line muffin cups. in large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, dill weed, onion powder and salt.
In small bowl combine cottage cheese, milk, butter and egg until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan. Makes 12 muffins.

title: easy cheese biscuits(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add cheese, dry mustard and red pepper; stir. Add milk and stir with a fork until dough leaves sides of bowl. Turn dough onto floured board and knead just until smooth. Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with 2-inch cutter. Bake on greased pan with edges slightly touching for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon mold
directions: Drain salmon; pick out bones and skin.
Add celery, olives, hard-boiled eggs, salt, paprika and lemon juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
Blend in mayonnaise and pour over salmon mixture, stirring to coat.
Pour into a wet mold (fish mold if available).
Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: salad dressing(dressing for potato salad)
directions: In a sauce pan whip together all ingredients. Milk is add gradually. Turn on heat. Stir constantly with wooden spoon about 5 minutes. or until thick.

title: mushroom potatoes
directions: Blend together soup, milk and pepper.
Grease a 2-quart casserole or 9 x 12-inch dish. Arrange layer of potatoes, onion and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Dot mushrooms and butter on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil. Bake 15 minutes more. Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut up.
Mix sour cream, soup and chicken. Crush crackers; mix crackers and poppy seed.
Put over top.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: finnish coffee bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon of sugar. Let stand until dissolved. Heat milk until just warm.
Melt butter.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in two cups boiling water.
Add water to pineapple juice to make one cup and stir into Jell-O.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Let jell.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread cheese mixture on set Jell-O and sprinkle with pecans.

title: hobo soup
directions: Wash lentils; add stock and salt.
Cover and simmer on low heat until tender, about 1 hour.
Add other ingredients and cover. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Melt butter in 9x13 pan. Beat egg whites gradually adding sugar until stiff. Fold nuts into beaten egg whites, then fold into butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Mix all together in large bowl, except ginger ale and sherbet. Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.

title: eggs florentine(diabetic recipe)
directions: Spray individual baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Cover bottom with spinach or broccoli.
Add egg, salt and pepper. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until white is set.

title: pork medallions with dijon dill sauce
directions: Cut pork crosswise into 4 pieces.
To make medallions, place each piece of pork, cut side down, on flat surface; cover with waxed paper and flatten gently with heel of hand to 3/4-inch thickness.
Panbroil pork in nonstick frypan over medium high heat, about 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Remove medallions to warm platter; season with garlic salt and pepper on both sides.

title: venison mincemeat "son-of-a-gun style"
directions: Cook in large black kettle until suet meat melts.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: graham cracker cookie
directions: Lay graham crackers (with sides touching) on a cookie sheet with sides.
Melt butter and margarine with sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cover crackers with pecan bits.
Drizzle butter mixture over the graham crackers.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Take off cookie sheet immediately and put on foil to protect your counters.
(Very sticky.)

title: special k bars
directions: Measure corn syrup and brown sugar into a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and raisins.
Add Kellogg's Special K cereal.
Stir until well coated.
With back of a spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Let stand until cool. Cut into bars.

title: gourmet meat loaf
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, cook onions and garlic in butter.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, and 1/3 c. ketchup.
Cook for 2 - 3 minutes until onions are tender.
In a large bowl, combine meats, bread crumbs, and eggs.
Add onion mixture and mix.
Pat into a baking dish.
Spread remaining 1/3 ketchup over the top and bake for 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together.
Then add eggs, vanilla wafers, pecans and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Heat nonstick Pam sprayed skillet over medium-high heat and brown and cook balls.
Remove and keep warm.
Pour any fat from pan.
Mix cornstarch and sugar. Stir into reserved syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth. Pour into skillet, cooking over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickened and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper; heat through.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix Parkay, cream cheese, sugar and salt; add eggs one at a time to mix.
Add flour and vanilla to mix as well.
Bake in Bundt pan greased with Pam at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: squash pickle
directions: Sprinkle squash with salt. Let stand for 1 hour and drain. Bring all other ingredients to a boil and pour over squash. Return to heat and bring back to a boil. Pack in jars and seal.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions. Combine beef and evaporated milk.
Divide meat mixture into 5 patties.
On waxed paper, flatten each to a 6-inch circle.
Spoon 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each. Draw edges over stuffing and seal. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, combine soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until it bubbles.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: tuna-onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix prepared macaroni and cheese with onion, soup, mushrooms, olives and 1/2 can of onions.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over casserole and return to oven.
Raise temperature to 450°.
Bake 10 more minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip and powdered sugar, then pour into graham cracker shell.
After that, cool in refrigerator.
If you want, you could put Hershey's syrup in two circle forms, then lightly put knife through.

title: homemade apple cider
directions: In crock-pot, mix apple juice and tea together.
Leaving rind on, slice orange into thin pieces.
Stick whole cloves into orange slices.
Let float on top of mixture.
Put cinnamon sticks in and let cook on low all day.
Makes for a warm evening beverage and fills the house with a wonderful aroma.

title: polka dot cake
directions: Mix hot water and dates.
Let cool.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with date mixture.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over top and bake.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add 1 cup raisins and 1 or 2 tablespoons caraway seed to flour mixture.
Add buttermilk and melted butter to beaten egg mixture.
Add to flour mixture. Combine well; pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: wheat graham bread
directions: Beat well.
Knead.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead again.
Let rise.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cover with foil last 20 minutes, if necessary.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Season to taste and serve. Serves 10.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine sugar, flour, baking soda, spices and walnuts in a bowl. In a large
bowl, mix egg, molasses, buttermilk and melted butter. Add dry ingredients and stir until blended. Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake for 20 minutes, until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie crust (deep dish) at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325°.
Bake until set in center, about 30 to 45 minutes.
(Can use half of spices if too strong.)

title: jiffy creamed chicken
directions: Grease and set aside 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cube bread and toss in butter; set aside.
Drain peas, reserving liquid and place in large saucepan.
Blend in and heat thoroughly chicken, cream of mushroom soup, reserved liquid, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole and top with buttered bread.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bread is browned.

title: ice cream(one gallon)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, eggs and milk together; cook in double boiler until thickened.
Add vanilla, cream and Junket tablets.
Mix thoroughly and then allow to cool.
Pour in freezer container and prepare according to directions.
For fruit flavored, add 1 quart crushed fruit.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned peas, green beans and corn.
Add diced cucumber, green pepper, onion, celery and pimentos.

title: baked beans
directions: Add crumbled bacon to beans along with other ingredients. Bake at 375° until desired thickness.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins; cool, peel and cut into strips. In saucepan ove low heat, combine cheese and butter; stir until almost melted. Remove from heat; blend in remaining ingredients. Fold potatoes into mixture; turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Mix apples, lemon juice and sugar; pour over bread.
Beat butter, brown sugar, 1 cup white sugar, flour mixture and eggs.
Pour over apples and bread.
Bake until done.

title: ham with apple raisin sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in 1 large (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add chopped apples, apple juice, raisins, brown sugar and cinnamon to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend.
Insert whole cloves in top of ham if desired.
Place ham in bag on top of sauce.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top.
Bake until meat thermometer registers 140° or ham is heated through, 1 to 1 3/4 hours.
Let stand in bag 5 minutes.
Serve with sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels with water and butter in covered double boiler or in a saucepan over low heat.
(I use microwave.)
Combine sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add caramel mixture (after cooling a little) and mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pie filling will appear to be very soft, but becomes firmer as it cools.

title: senior citizen breakfast muffins
directions: Soak bran flakes in milk, 3 minutes or until soft.
Add well beaten egg, oil and flour.
Mix well until all lumps are out.
Add the butter flavoring.
Mix in well.
Pour mixture into a 12-muffin cup pan.
Be sure to spray each cup with a cooking spray or use paper liners before filling.

title: zippy shrimp spread
directions: Bring water to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain well; rinse with cold water. Chill.
Peel; devein shrimp.
Reserve 3 shrimp for garnish. Coarsely chop remaining shrimp.
Set aside.

title: lazy fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo
and	pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour,
baking
powder
and milk; pour into dish.
Pour fruit and juice in last.
Bake for about 1 hour at 250°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers with peelings on in 1/2 cup salt and water to cover for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: chicken breasts with artichoke hearts
directions: On waxed paper, coat chicken breasts with 1/4 cup flour.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken until lightly browned on all sides.
Place chicken in a 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hayride kitchen bean soup
directions: Mix together and simmer 3 hours.

title: english trifle
directions: Soak jelly roll in sherry.
Lay it in bottom of dish.
When 1st jello is slightly cool, pour over cake.
Mix fruit with second jello.
When first jello is completely set, add second jello with fruit.
When that layer is completely set add vanilla pudding. Cover with wax paper to avoid skim forming.
Add layer of whipped cream.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: sarahs shrimp bisque
directions: Heat butter over medium heat, add shells cook 10 - 12 minute until pink. Add onions cook for 5 to 6 minutes Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add tomato paste, paprika & cayenne cook until glossy, 3 - 4 minutes. Add brandy. Cook down to a paste. Add flour make a rue. Cook for 6 - 8 minutes. Gradually add heavily salted fish stock whisk and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until thick 1 hour. This can be made ahead. Before serving strain, add cream shrimp sherry, salt and pepper. Cook 3 - 4 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Press in tube pan that is sprayed with Pam.

title: pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain peas and asparagus.
Put 1 can peas in bottom of casserole dish.
Add asparagus and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour mushroom soup over top and add second layer and another layer of cheese. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix a little margarine with crushed saltines.
Spread over top of casserole for last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Bake at 350°.

title: crab wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place crab, vegetables and 2 tablespoons of the butter in a frying pan and saute until limp. Set aside.
Melt the remaining butter in a medium saucepan and blend in 2 tablespoons flour.
Add one cup milk gradually, making a smooth white sauce.
Add a little juice from the crab and set aside.
Put 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl. Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add 3/4 cup milk to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly a few seconds.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick in a large rectangle.
Add 1/3 cup of the white sauce to the crab and vegetable mixture and spread it over the dough.
Roll up along the long end and place seam side down on a baking sheet.
Brush with egg and water that has been beaten together.
Bake the Wellington 25 to 30 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and thyme to the remaining white sauce.
Let Wellington rest 10 minutes before slicing into 2-inch slices.
Serve warm sauce on the side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar in a bowl.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve pudding
mix in milk, mix until thick.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: blueberry swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and egg whites.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Reserve 1 cup of pie filling for topping. Spoon remaining pie filling randomly over cake batter.
Marble by pulling knife through batter in wide curves, then turn pan and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Serve with dollops of whipped topping and reserved pie filling.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread butter or margarine in pie plate. Brown meat and onion; drain and place in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Bake 25 minutes. Spread tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter at 250 degrees.
Add sugar and slivered almonds. Stir with a wooden spoon while sugar melts and blends with butter. Slowly turn up heat.
Cook until caramel in color (30-40 minutes).
If butter separates, continue cooking.
Pour into jelly roll pan (extremely hot).
Break up 1/2 Hershey bar and spread on top of hot toffee.
Sprinkle with 1/2 ground almonds.
Set until cold.
Turn over on waxed paper and spread other side with 1/2 Hershey bar (melt in microwave).
Top with ground almonds.
Break into bite-sized pieces.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Chop onion. Layer in order given.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Pat in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: wild blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine in large bowl and sit aside to prepare pastry.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and bake in tube cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn into a large mixing bowl.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a deep saucepan.
Stir over heat, stirring constantly at 200°.
Cook until small amount of syrup turns brittle when dropped in ice cold water.
Remove from heat; stir in butter. Pour over popcorn and shape into individual balls.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cut butter into flour and baking soda as for pie crust.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine; saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the ripe olives, green chiles, sour cream and soup; mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup sauce; set aside.
Fold in chicken or turkey and 1/2 cup of cheese to remaining sauce.
Warm tortillas as directed on package. Fill tortillas with chicken or turkey mixture.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In small bowl, combine reserved 3/4 cup sauce and milk; spoon over tortillas. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
To serve, sprinkle with remaining cheese and olives.
Makes 8 enchiladas.

title: meatball soupstilwell, kansas
directions: In a large pot, heat broth to simmer.
Meanwhile, mix beef, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape in 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: peanut butter & jelly cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the Shortening, Peanut Butter, Sugar, Brown Sugar and Egg.
Add the Flour, Baking Soda, Baking Powder, and Salt.
Cover and chill.
Preheat oven to 375.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Press thumb into center.
Bake for 10 - 12 minutes.
Spoon small amount of Jelly or Jam into each thumbprint.
Yield:
approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk, flour, salt, baking powder and fat or oil.
Add 1 cup whole kernel corn.
Blend; drop by spoonful into hot fat.
Cook until nice and brown on both sides.

title: diabetic pickled cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into smaller flowerets; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan and boil for 10 minutes.
Pour over cauliflower and let cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, raisins and bacon together gently. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar thoroughly.
Fold dressing into vegetable mixture and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: homemade pastry recipe
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl; cut in shortening.
Gradually add cold water, mixing until flour is moistened.
Shape dough into ball; flatten to 1-inch thick.
On lightly floured board, roll dough into a circle about 2 inches larger than inverted 9-inch pie plate.
Line plate with pastry, then turn edge under.
Flute, if desired.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs singly, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to the creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream and blending after each addition.
Spread half of batter in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lined on the bottom with wax paper.
Cream butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add nuts; mix well.
Sprinkle half of nut mixture evenly over batter in pan.
Cover with remaining batter, then sprinkle on remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until done.
Yield:
One tall coffee cake.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole, combine potatoes, onion, celery and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Fold into potato mixture.
Top with bacon.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes, then place under broiler to crisp bacon.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup, butter and vinegar together until brittle stage.
Drop a little in a cold glass of water; if it's crisp, it's ready.
Have lots of popcorn ready in a big pan.
Pour some of the syrup mixture over corn; stir with spoon.
With buttered hands, press into balls like you make a snowball.
Pour more syrup on corn and repeat.

title: ice cream-jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add the ice cream; stir until melted.
Stir in the fruit cocktail and walnuts.
Spoon into an 8 x 8-inch square pan and refrigerate.
To serve, cut into squares and place on lettuce leaf.
Nuts and cherries may be used for garnish.

title: healthy caesar salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all together very well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased hot skillet.
Brown on both sides.

title: norma's banana ice cream
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Beat eggs, salt and sugar.
Add to milk.
Cook until mixture coats the spoon.
Remove.
Cool.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Add half and half.
Add to milk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Mash bananas.
Add to mixture. Freeze using ice cream maker.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: apricot bars(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, brown sugar and oats.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, buttered.
Spread with jam.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberry sauce. Spoon sour cream on top and stir to marbelize.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian "s" cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well with each addition.
Mix in vanilla and cream; mix well.
Stir in baking powder.
Stir in flour a little at a time until a dough forms.
It should not be too dry or too sticky. Take small amounts of dough and roll with hands to form an "S". Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 13 minutes, until light golden color and firm to touch.
Depending on size, can make 150 to 240 cookies.
Once baked, they freeze well for approximately 6 months.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetable mix a little bit; drain and cool.
Add onion and peppers and mix.
Mix sugar and vinegar together until sugar melts.
Then add oil.
Pour over the vegetables and onion and pepper.
Let set overnight.
Will keep good for 3 or 4 days.

title: mexican soup
directions: In a large pot, add minestrone soup, Ranch style beans, stewed Mexican tomatoes, whole kernel corn and water.
Saute onion, celery and ground meat.
Drain well and add to minestrone soup mixture with chili powder.

title: iced herb tea
directions: Bring to a boil the water and tea bags.
Remove from heat. Let sit for 5 minutes.
Pour into medium pitcher and add water to fill. Add lemon and sugar. Tastes like cherry Kool-Aid.

title: fried squash medley
directions: Mix together and bread evenly.
Cook in skillet for 15 to 20 minutes in oil or bacon grease or until brown.

title: chili
directions: Cool ground beef, drain well. Cook onions and peppers together in boiler. Add to ground beef. Add the rest of the ingredients and cook for 1 hour.
tags: pack of chili o seasoning mix

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: The day before or at least 2 hours before serving, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.
Good with hamburgers, hot dogs or grilled fish.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in candy pieces and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by half teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Remove from baking sheet and place on wire rack to cool.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: baked clams
directions: Preheat broiler.
Fill clam shells with clams.
Blend together butter, salt and pepper, garlic, shallot, parsley and thyme. Spoon an equal amount of herb butter on top of each clam shell. Smooth slightly and arrange the shells on a baking sheet.
Blend the bread crumbs and cheese; sprinkle over each shell.
Place under broiler 5 inches from heat and broil 3 minutes.
Set oven to 450° and bake about 2 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese, oleo and milk.
Add chilies and then pour over corn mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
This salad gets better the more time it is allowed to marinate in the refrigerator.

title: easy cheese roll
directions: You will need waxed paper.

title: garlic pickles
directions: Drain the pickles and cut into 3/4 inch slices.
Place the pickles in a large pottery container or other non reactive container.
Separate the garlic bulb into cloves, peel and add to the pickles.
Add the sugar, mustard seeds, cinnamon sticks and peppercorn and mix well.
Let the pickles cure for 3 weeks, stirring daily.
Keep refrigerated.

title: marinade
directions: Spread on
meat.
I
use round steak or a London broil. Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Broil.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Trim ends of zucchini. Cut them lengthwise in half.
Cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and let stand.
Scoop out the insides and chop.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Add chopped zucchini, some of bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper, garlic powder and add the eggs.
Mix all together.
Stuff the zucchini halves with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Pour a little oil, beaten egg, bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; hold.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, soda and salt and add to first mix and beat well.
Add carrots, coconut, pineapple, pecans and raisins. Bake in 3 layer pans (greased and floured) at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool completely and frost.

title: autumn vegetable soup
directions: In Dutch oven or kettle, saute garlic in olive oil.
Add chopped vegetables, salt, ground pepper and cayenne.
Stir intermittently over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add stock or water.
Bring to a boil; lower to a simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until everything is tender.
Add Swiss chard or collard greens, chopped tomato and bell pepper.
Simmer another 5 minutes.
Add herbs, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Continue to simmer another 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream or yogurt just before serving. Garnish each bowl with sunflower seeds and parsley.
This is a terrific main dish!
Don't limit yourself to the vegetables listed. Try chopped turnips, parsnips, zucchini, pumpkin, acorn squash or kohlrabi.

title: cherry salad
directions: Select large cherries.
Wash and remove stones carefully. Fill with mixture of cream cheese and chopped nuts.
Chill. Serve on lettuce with fruit dressing.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix liquids and butter; add potatoes and onions. Cook until done, 12 to 15 minutes. Mix cracker crumbs and seasonings. Add to potato and onion mixture. Add peppers. Mix well; bring to a boil. Add cream and corn. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with corn meal muffins. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: jello salad
directions: Dump pineapple in pot.
Sprinkle Jell-O on pineapple.
Put on stove and let get hot (don't boil).
Set off and cool, then mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: honey wheat bread(serves 10)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a large mixing bowl for 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and next 6 ingredients.
Add whole wheat flour, beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in enough batter for bread flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead for 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in an oiled bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until dough has doubled in bulk.
Punch down dough; divide in half, shape into 2 loaves.
Place in 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 4-inch pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, until loaves sound hollow when tapped on.

title: one pan pork chop supper
directions: In electric skillet, brown chops.
Parboil potatoes 10 minutes. Cut in half and add to pork chops.
Add drained green beans.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper to soup.
Mix in milk. Pour over chops, potatoes and beans.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Defrost and drain spinach, pressing to remove excess liquid. Mix with remaining ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking dish.
Microwave 2 minutes on High or bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
These may be frozen before baking but no longer than 2 weeks.

title: blueberry-yogurt muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Combine orange juice, oil, vanilla, yogurt and egg.
Stir well.
Add to dry ingredients. Gently fold in blueberries.
Coat muffin tin with cooking spray. Divide batter into 12 muffin cups.
Sprinkle tops with sugar. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes and tops are golden brown.
Remove from pan and let cool on wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese patties
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Add remaining three. Make into small balls; press flat with a fork. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples in water or apple cider until soft; strain and mash into a pulp. To each cup of pulp, add 1/2 cup of sugar and stir in 3 teaspoons cinnamon, 1 1/2 teaspoons cloves, 1/2 teaspoon allspice and sugar to taste. Cook over low heat, stirring often, until mixture sheets from a spoon.

title: corn-sausage chowder
directions: In Dutch oven cook sausage & onion till sausage is brown and onion is tender; drain on paper towels.
Return sausage & onion to pan with potatoes, salt, marjoram, pepper and water.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat & simmer just until potato is tender, about 15 minutes.
Add corns and evaporated milk.
Heat through.

title: potato patties
directions: Stir 2 cups of cold water into potatoes; stir in margarine and rest of ingredients.
Fry in greased skillet until brown.

title: shake and bake
directions: Makes enough to coat about 4 pounds of chicken.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, peanut butter and graham crackers on stove.
Mix well until done.
Take away from heat and let cool. Make balls.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and 1/2 bar of wax.
Dip in balls and put on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: ranch dip with vegetables
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make dressing and
pour
over broccoli, bacon, raisins, seeds and onion.	Mix well.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
While macaroni is cooking, saute onion in a little margarine.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: May use any flavor jello; I use lemon, orange, lime and cherry.

title: holland carrot bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Put in bowl and make a well in center.
Add sugar, cooking oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Fold in carrots; don't pack in measuring cup.
Add nuts or raisins, if desired.
Turn into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven, 300°, about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 large loaf.
Can be baked in 2 smaller loaves.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt.
Add cooled milk.
Add dissolved yeast and beaten egg, then add flour and mix well.
Results will be like biscuit batter.
Place in the refrigerator overnight.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix as directed and bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cake is done.
Set cake aside to cool.
Mix sugar, Crisco, salt, oleo, vanilla and milk with hand mixer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mixture will look curdled but it will get fluffy; just keep mixing it.
Spread mixture over top of cooled cake.
Next, melt can of chocolate frosting over low heat and pour on top.
Serve chilled.

title: ham & cheese ballwarren, texas
directions: Soften cream cheese and add worchester sauce.
Add green onions chopped fine.
Add chopped ham.
Roll into 2 balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus on platter or baking dish.
Season to taste. Chop pimientos and spread over asparagus.
Top with cheese spread or soup of your choice.
Put in oven until cheese is melted.
This makes a pretty dish.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar in a large bowl; beat well until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and 2 tablespoons milk; beat well.
Prepare one envelope whipped topping mix as directions say, using 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in peanut butter mixture and spoon into pie shell.
Prepare other envelope of whipped topping mix as directions say, using remaining 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon evenly over peanut butter mixture.
Chill at least 5 hours before serving.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Boil liquids and spices for 5 minutes. Put sliced tomatoes into pt. jars. Pour hot liquid over tomatoes and seal. Makes about 10 pt.

title: country steak and chili gravy
directions: Trim off all fat from meat; pound with meat mallet or edge of saucer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip into egg, then into crushed corn flakes mixed with chili powder.
Heat oil in large skillet; brown meat on both sides.
Add onion and green pepper. Pour in tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter, sugar and Karo. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, baking soda and salt to butter mixture. Spray a roasting pan with Pam and put popcorn in.
Pour mixture over popcorn and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break apart.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine Pet milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread.
Beat some while spreading on cake.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
(Good on German chocolate cake mix cake.)

title: royal pecan pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cover edge of pie shell for last 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, except the sour cream.
Pour half of the mixture into a dish and refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream on top of congealed mixture.
Pour other half of mixture on top of sour cream. Refrigerate until firm.

title: golden rule cake
directions: Put lard into saucepan. Add salt and spices; boil 3 minutes. Cool, then add flour, baking powder and soda (dissolved in 3 tablespoons warm water).
Fold in nuts.
Turn into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Melt butter with olive oil and garlic until cloves are soft. Remove cloves.
Evenly coat chicken with spices.
Roll chicken in sour cream.
Cover evenly with bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in olive oil and butter.
Remove from stove and place in preheated (350°) oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Fettucini Alfredo.

title: western beef casserole au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper; blend well.
Spoon into greased dish.
Spoon corn evenly over meat.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Combine remaining ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high setting 3 to 4 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk in saucepan.
Add raisins if desired. Mix to moisten rice.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add nutmeg if desired.
Add hot rice mixture slowly and mix well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water and bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
Stir several times during the first 20 minutes of baking.
Serve hot or cold.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together oil and sugar.
Then add remaining ingredients, folding in the apples and nuts.
Pour in oblong dish (9 x 11-inch or 13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: real old-time strawberry shortcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine the egg and the light cream and add to the mixture, stirring just until the dough follows the fork around the bowl.
On a lightly floured surface, pat or roll to a 1-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cutter. Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Split the shortcake and spread cut sides with butter.
Spoon berries between the cakes and on top.
Cover with fresh whipped cream.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk; heat if you need to cook quicker.
Add onions, potatoes and carrots; season to taste.
Put dots of butter on top.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: robbie's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill well before serving.

title: czech beef dinner
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge beef in mixture and brown in hot oil.
Pour off drippings and add onion, garlic, dill weed, caraway seed, paprika and water.
Cover loosely and cook slowly for 2 hours until meat is tender.
Stir in sour cream and heat through, but do not boil.
Heat sauerkraut in a saucepan, drain and place on platter.
Serve meat mixture over sauerkraut. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: instant party potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, bring water, butter and salt to a boil.
Add milk, cream cheese, sour cream, garlic powder and minced onion. Stir in potato flakes.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: whipped potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, mash the potatoes.
Add the cream cheese, sour cream, butter, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Transfer to a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: red pepper pasta with smoked chicken
directions: Whisk first 6 ingredients together and fold in olives to marinate 8 to 12 hours.
Cook pasta; drain well and toss with olives and dressing.
Let cool to room temperature.
Fold in chicken, green onions, corn and parsley.
Season to taste with pepper.
When ready to serve, spoon into a shallow bowl or platter.
Sprinkle top of salad with the cheese and beans.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: russian t cakes(cookies)
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla; add mix of flour, salt and nuts. Chill; then roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake until set.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Stir milk, sugar and Karo over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
When mixture boils, reduce heat to low and stir constantly until mixture forms a soft ball.
Add dates and cook until ball forms again.
Let cool.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour on waxed paper about 2 feet long and roll.

title: hearty black-eyed pea soup
directions: Cook sausage, beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Yields 12-16 servings or about 4 quarts.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cool.
Add the chilies, tomato, onion and soup; mix together.
Lay tortillas in greased casserole dish. Top with chicken mixture.
Cover generously with cheese.
Sprinkle taco sauce over top (use the amount that suits your taste).
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Chop tomatoes, cucumbers, green peppers and onions.
Add to spaghetti.
Add one bottle Italian dressing and one Salad Supreme.

title: caramel apples
directions: In top of double boiler or saucepan, combine caramels and water.
Cook until melted, stirring occasionally.
Insert wooden sticks into stem end of each apple.
Keep caramel mixture over low heat.
Dip apples into caramel mixture, turning to coat.
Scrape off excess caramel mixture when removing apple from pan.
Place on greased waxed paper and chill until set.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook chicken with 2 ribs of celery, onion, bay leaf, salt and enough water to cover.
Cook until done. Remove chicken and strain stock.
Cut chicken into large pieces. Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add enough chicken stock, stirring constantly to desired consistency.
Divide chicken and cooked vegetables between 2 deep-dish pie plates.
Add sauce, lifting chicken and vegetables so sauce flows down.
Top each pie plate with a prepared pie crust or one from scratch.
Mix egg and milk and brush pastry with egg wash.
Puncture pastry with fork in several places to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown.
Serve piping hot.

title: firehouse chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan; boil for about 4 hours. Place baked wings in Tupperware container and pour in sauce.
Cover and shake. Remove chicken wings and serve.

title: holiday side dish
directions: Make according to size of dish needed.
Cut up all vegetables and apples.
Stir in raisins.
Stir in sugar or just sprinkle over the top of the vegetables.
Generously sprinkle with cinnamon. Pour honey over the top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Cool. Combine dressing, cheese, onion, basil, salt and pepper.
In large bowl, place pasta, peas and tomato.
Add dressing mixture.
Stir lightly to coat.
Garnish with olives.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: stuffing
directions: Melt oleo.
Add celery, onions, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Mix with cornbread.
Add giblets and meat from neck, well cooked.
For more moisture, add drippings from turkey.
For more seasoning and spicy taste, add a package of seasoned bread cubes. Bake at 350°.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste with sauce every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and golden.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: oreo cookie bomb-out
directions: Smash cookies coarsely.
Let vanilla ice cream melt until soft.
Fold all together and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or metal cake pan.
Slice to serve. Easy and good!!

title: pecan crunch
directions: Coarsely chop 1 cup of pecans; finely chop other pecans. Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix coarsely chopped and 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans with baking soda.
Set aside.

title: celeste's mushroom salade
directions: Slice mushrooms thickly just before serving.
Mix with chopped parsley, garlic, oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Use two times as much oil as lemon juice.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat with onion, green pepper and add salt and pepper when done, add catsup and simmer.
Serve on hot buns.

title: easy coleslaw
directions: Mix together salad dressing, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add prepared mustard (optional).
Pour over cabbage and carrot.
Mix well.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Flavor with love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith, blending very well.
Fold into daily life.
Bake with the warmth of human kindness and serve with a smile anytime.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken and place in bottom of dish. Cut eggs and put on top.
Mix stock and soup and heat together.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Tear chicken in bite size pieces, then put in ungreased baking dish.
Add vegetables rinsed with hot water.
Pour over chicken, then mix 1 cup milk, Bisquick mix and melted margarine; put over chicken and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar until stiff.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 20 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips until smooth.
Remove peanut butter and form small balls (quarter size).
Use toothpicks to dip balls.
Chill on sheet of wax paper.
Yields 30 to 40.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes, eggs, sugar and milk.
Add nuts and coconut. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes in a greased casserole dish.
Garnish with marshmallows.
Put casserole back in oven and melt the marshmallows, then serve.

title: garlic wonton crisps
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to boil in large pot.
Add half wontons one at a time.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove carefully to large bowl cold water.
Do same with remaining wontons.

title: almond bark
directions: Place chocolate in 1-quart glass measure or mixing bowl. Microwave at 70% power 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in almonds.
Pour immediately onto foil or cookie sheet.
Spread thinly.
Cool for approximately 1 hour.
Break into pieces to serve.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first four ingredients in a large bowl and stir in butter until well mixed.
Add buttermilk and egg; mix well.
Knead on a floured board for 1 minute.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick and cut into 6-inch rounds.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Blend margarine, flour, sugar and salt with pastry cutter. Add pecans.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle crushed pineapple over this.
Top with whipping cream.
Chill.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar; blend well.
Add eggs.
Mix a small amount of the flour and baking powder; add to mixture, then add as much flour as needed.
Roll out dough and cut to desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian cracker snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place crackers in a large, shallow baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine butter, salad dressing mix, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour butter mixture over crackers; stir well.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Pour onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container. Yields 4 cups.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all together and store in jar.
Add 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: skillet steak strips
directions: Slice beef into 1/2-inch strips.
Heat oil in large skillet. Brown beef and remove.
In same skillet, saute onion and garlic adding more oil if necessary.
Stir in ketchup, water, vinegar, bay leaf, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, pepper, cloves and raisins.
Add browned beef, cover and simmer 1 hour or until beef is tender. Discard bay leaf.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Do not grease or flour pan.
Blend in a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan with a fork.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Mix with all other dry ingredients, then add milk and eggs.
Roll out in balls.
Cook 10 minutes in butter.
Put in crock-pot and let simmer in barbecue sauce, approximately for 1 hour.

title: ground beef gravy
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in skillet.
Pour in cream of mushroom soup.
Serve over browned biscuits or add peas and serve over noodles.
Great and easy!
