title: salve for burns, frostbite, chapped hands, etc.
directions: Melt oil and wax together and put in the turpentine when sufficiently cooled.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg, butter and nuts. Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream confectioners sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Spread over crust mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and mix with Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Add raw grated carrots and nuts.
Bake in layers from 30 to 40 minutes in 300° oven.

title: reese bars
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter in a double boiler.
Add graham crackers and powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Press firmly into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and place in 350° oven for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread melted chips.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except seasonings.
Add seasonings to taste.
Hot peppers may be added if you want hotter dip.

title: chicken wing drumsticks
directions: Remove and discard wing tips.
Separate remaining wing sections.
Cut skin at small end of each wing section.
Pull out one of the bones from section having 2 bones; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, toast sesame seed over low heat until golden, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil fryer and debone.
Mix 2 cups broth and soup.
Put in baking dish.
Add Veg-All and chicken.
Then mix Bisquick, buttermilk and oil.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb-cherry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand until it makes its own juice.
Then boil 10 minutes.
Add 2 small packages jello and pie filling.
Heat again and put in jars.
Let cool and freeze in glass jam jars or small plastic containers.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: joanne's muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: white cookies
directions: Add dry ingredients together. Cream in shortening, then add eggs and milk (add 1 tsp. vinegar to sweet milk) and vanilla.
Can be made as drop cookies or roll out. If you roll them out refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle with white sugar before baking or frost after cooled. Bake at 350 for 12 minutes.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: Cook the butter and marshmallows over boiling water until syrupy, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Put Rice Krispies in greased large bowl and pour marshmallow mixture over them, stirring briskly.
Press into greased shallow pan. Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: potato latkas (pancakes)
directions: Shred potatoes and mix remaining ingredients.
Cook on hot griddle until browned.
Good with smoked sausage, homemade applesauce and slaw.

title: sam's turkey pot pie
directions: Dice potato, carrot, and celery. Boil in water for 10 minutes, drain. Add the peas, turkey, stock and the soup. Cook and stir for 7 minutes. Mixture should be thick. Add flour if necessary.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of melted margarine, pepper sauce and vinegar; put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with celery sticks and dressing for dipping.

title: scottish highland oat cakes
directions: Turn oven on to warm at 475°.
Start water boiling and when at a full boil pour 1/2 cup into small bowl.
Add the 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir to dissolve and set aside to add later in recipe.
Blend together the sugar, rolled oats, flour, baking powder, salt and bran flakes.
Cut in shortening.
Add the water and baking soda mixture and blend.
The mix will be sticky, so add extra flour and oats to make it easier to handle.
Prepare a flat surface with flour and oats and roll out dough 1/4 inch thin and cut with a two-inch round cookie cutter.
Place oat cakes on a cookie sheet and bake at 475° for 5 to 8 minutes until golden brown, taking care that the bottoms are not overly browned.
Serve hot out of the oven with clotted cream, butter or jam.

title: nut milk
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.
Nut milk can be used for all recipes that call for milk and just drink it.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sour cream, onion, chicken soup and egg; stir together.
Melt margarine and pour over dressing crumbs.
Put in layers in casserole dish, ending with dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan; spread pineapple on bottom.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit.
Add pecan halves.
Cut margarine into thick slices and lay on top of pecans.
Bake at 350° until brown, 45 minutes to one hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients.
Chill for 45 minutes before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain
sausage and bread.
Add mustard, salt, eggs, milk and
cheese.
(Add mushrooms and/or bell pepper, if desired.) Mix well
and
pour
into
8-inch
glass square pan. Refrigerate overnight.	Then
bake for 40 minutes uncovered at 350°.
Cover with foil.	Continue baking 15 minutes longer.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to the sugar and egg mixture, mixing well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Reserve the remainder.
Add nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Add remaining M&M's to each top of cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and chop;
combine sauerkraut, celery, green pepper, onions and
pimento in bowl.
Mix well.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and
pepper
in jar.
Mix well.
Add to sauerkraut mixture; mix
well
and
chill.
Salad will keep well in refrigerator up to a week.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat one minute each time eggs are added.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with milk; add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple lemon pie
directions: Combine lemon pudding and pie filling, undrained crushed pineapple, water and butter.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Pour into cooled graham cracker crust and chill until ready to serve.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Put in deep dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar. Spoon over margarine.
Spoon fruit on mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: banana loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients; add nuts to margarine last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in fat.
Place in shallow ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with celery, brown sugar, mustard, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour tomato sauce mixed with water over chops.
Cover and bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until chops are tender.

title: 10-bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Combine beans, 7 cups water, all seasonings and ham hocks in large gumbo pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce to simmer. Add onions, celery, garlic, tomatoes and peppers.
Simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Do not break peppers.
Remove ham hock; remove meat from bone and discard bones.
Add remaining meats, except shrimp.
Cook 1 1/2 hours longer.
Add shrimp the last 15 minutes.
Makes 12 (10-ounce) servings.
Freezes well.

title: date nut bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a medium bowl, stir together sugars, flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, corn oil and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in dates and nuts until well mixed.
Spread evenly in prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned and cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
While still warm, cut into 24 bars.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in dressing until light and fluffy. Add salt.
Serve with potatoes, chips or crackers.

title: slushy lemonade
directions: In blender container,
combine lemon juice and sugar with water.
Add ice to make 1 cup.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 1 serving.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Place in a casserole dish and bake in a 350° to 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raspberry-cranberry-burgundy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and make sure it is melted before adding Burgundy and pineapple. When mixture is partially set, add nuts and stir fruit up from the bottom of bowl.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve over ice.

title: potato soup(cuisinart recipe)
directions: Peel potatoes and using the slicing blade, slice the potatoes and onions.
Put into pot with the chicken broth.
Season to taste and bring to boil.
Turn to low and partially cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Place mixture in small batches in the bowl fitted with the steel chopping blade and puree. Put back into pot and add butter and cream; heat through but do not boil.
Serve with a garnish of minced chives.

title: neiman marcus squares
directions: Beat 1 egg.
Mix with cake mix and melted butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Add coconut and pecans.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325 ° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron. With wire whisk, mix first 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and beat until well mixed. Pour batter into center of lower half to about 1-inch from edges. Cover and bake according to waffle iron.

title: crescent italiano bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Put in 8-inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Separate dough into triangles.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done according to package directions. Drain and add ingredients.
Stir and toss.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add ginger ale and chill.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice for topping.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas to Jell-O mixture.
Chill until firm.
Combine juice, sugar, flour and egg in saucepan and cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and cool.
Fold in whipping cream that has been whipped; spread mixture over Jell-O.
Top with 1/4 cup shredded American cheese and 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.

title: tourtiere(french canadian)
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Add onions and saute until translucent.
Stir in remaining ingredients and let cool.
Spoon into pie plate and cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Simmer raisins in a little water for a few minutes.
Combine all but last ingredient and pour into buttered pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle this over pudding. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar with next 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned.
It may still be soft.
Cool well before cutting.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Then eggs.
Drain pineapple chunks.
Use juice.
Add water if not 2 cups, then heat.
When thickened, add pineapple and marshmallows, If you like, add 1/4 cup of walnuts.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix all together; spread onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Remove from oven when touching lightly leaves a print.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all dried ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
Take 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mix to make one steaming hot mug of cocoa.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple; sprinkle pineapple on bottom of an oblong cake pan.
Spread pie filling over the top of pineapple.
Cover pie filling with dry cake mix.
Cut butter into small squares; lay on top of dry cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of butter and cake mix.
Cook at least 45 minutes in a preheated 250° oven, or until done.

title: toll house cupcakes
directions: Combine and beat until creamy butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Spoon by rounded tablespoonful into paper lined 2 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Remove from oven and put 1 tablespoon of topping on each cupcake.
Return to oven and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushroom caps.
Cut up and brown with sausage; drain.
Mix sausage and stems with Mozzarella cheese and bread crumbs.
Stuff caps and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients well in pan.
Refrigerate.
Take out once a day and mix well for 3 days.
On the fourth day, form into 4 or 5 rolls in loaf pans or on broiler pan.
Bake at 150° for 12 hours. Eat and enjoy.

title: ritz cracker snacks
directions: Heat nuts, dates and milk in saucepan until thick and dates are dissolved.
Spread over crackers.
Bake on cookie sheets for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook puddings together with the orange juice concentrate and 3 cups liquid (reserved juice from fruits plus enough water to make 3 cups).
Cool.
Add fruit.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except apples.
When well mixed, add the apples.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple mint iced tea
directions: Combine pineapple juice, brewed tea and lemon slices.
Chill, serve over ice in glass.

title: mantequilla de pokre(pico de gallo with avocado)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a dip with tostados.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add to remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, beating until well blended. Fold in topping.
Ladle into crust, sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze firm before serving.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Blend cream cheese and sugar; stir in pineapple juice.
Add vanilla pudding and stir in crushed pineapple.
Pour into crust.
Chill; top with Cool Whip.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with sliced apples, slightly sweetened.
Press the remaining mixture over apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli and crab meat casserole
directions: Grease bottom and side of casserole size pan or casserole dish with butter or margarine.
Place separated broccoli on bottom of pan.
Layer crab meat on top; layer the soup on top of the crab meat (water the inside of the soup can slightly to assure obtaining all the soup); sprinkle grated
Cheddar cheese and then place croutons on top.
Cover with aluminum foil or dish top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and allow to set a few minutes before serving.
Yields 4 large servings or 8 small servings.

title: "that"
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until evenly browned, stirring frequently.
Pour off excess grease.
Add the onion, potatoes, green beans and seasonings to the ground beef.
Stir, cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are done.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Yields about 1 3/4 cups.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, seasoned salt, lemon juice and pepper sauce until blended.
Stir in crabmeat.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving to blend flavors.
Serve cold with crackers or chips. Makes about 2 cups.

title: bacon cheese puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread on cocktail rye bread slices (I use bread sticks sliced about an inch thick).
Bake at 350° about 5 minutes or until bubbly.

title: coconut-cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar and butter.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups baking mix.
Press in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Pour half of batter in pan, then sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon.
Then add rest of batter.
Bake at 350°.
Try 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: Mix meat loaf.
Cover with catsup.
Cook in aluminum pan at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, margarine, salt and vinegar in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add the sugar.
As the mixture thickens, you may need to use your hands to mix.
Add pecans and coconut.
Roll into balls and dip in Chocolate Coating.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Heat skillet to medium-high.
Add clarified butter. Saute salmon 2 minutes. Turn and saute 2 more minutes. Add white wine, dill, salt and pepper.
Cook until salmon flakes when tested. Serve with the pan juices.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously spray bottoms of 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 6 little loaf pans (3-inch).
Beat all ingredients on low speed 1 minute.
Beat medium 1 minute.
Pour into pans. Bake 2 large loaf pans 1 hour or 6 mini loaves 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Cool completely before slicing.

title: orange poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to mixture, alternating with milk.
Beat well after each.
Fold in poppy seed, vanilla and orange zest.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Add milk; cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens. Add salt, pepper, mustard and lemon juice.
Combine sauce with tuna, chopped onion, parsley, celery salt and cooked rice.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Beat egg slightly and add water.
Roll croquettes in crumbs then egg mixture, then again in crumbs.
Fry until golden brown (about 3 minutes).

title: after-school nachos
directions: Top chips with cheese.
Put under broiler or in microwave oven until cheese is melted.
If using a microwave oven, the cheese will melt in 30 seconds.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Take butter and melt.
Add onion finely chopped and saute.
Add flour and make a paste.
Add milk and slowly pour in.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Take Velveeta and dice up (saving a small portion for topping).
Lightly grease a Pyrex or Corning Ware pan and add macaroni, liquid and cheese; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Last 15 minutes add the extra cheese on top and bake, uncovered.
This recipe can easily be doubled.

title: paste for homes and schools
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and alum; stir in water.
Cook over double boiler until thick.
Stir often to keep from sticking. Remove from heat and add 15 drops of oil of cloves.
Store in jars, covered!

title: cheese puff sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange 4 slices bread in a greased baking pan.
Top with cheese.
Cover with other four slices of bread.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and continue to beat.
Add seasonings.
Pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate until eggs are absorbed.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Mix nuts, wheat squares, Cheerios, Rice Chex, pretzel bits and Slim Jims together.
Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and seasoned salt together; heat until smooth.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Bake in slow oven (200° to 250°) for 2 hours. Stir occasionally, being careful not to crush.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix ingredients all together in one bowl.
Beat until smooth. Preheat oven at 325°.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients; chill and serve.
Delicious with raw veggies!

title: virginia apple pudding
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole.
Combine next 6 ingredients to make batter; pour onto butter.
Drain apples; pile in center of batter.
Bake until batter covers fruit and crust browns.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat first 3 ingredients until stiff. Add sugar slowly.
Beat for 15 minutes or until stiff.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet. Use oleo to grease.
Put in preheated oven.
Turn off oven.
Leave 5 hours or overnight.
Do not open oven before time is up.

title: mammy's quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add milk and vanilla flavoring.
Mix all ingredients well with wire whisk.
Pour in baking dish.
Add fruit on top of mixture and top with margarine. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut shortening into the dry mixture.
Dissolve yeast in a little water, then stir in buttermilk.
Add to dry mixture; mix until smooth dough is formed.
Refrigerate in a greased covered bowl a few hours or overnight.
Make into rolls.
Place on greased pan. Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350 or 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add egg and stir all together.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Shape into balls; place on a cookie sheet and flatten with a fork dipped in sugar or shape in balls (do not flatten). Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
When removed from oven, push chocolate candy kisses in center of each cookie.
Remove silver foil from kisses ahead of time.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dice green pepper and onion.
Put in a soup kettle with the butter.
Saute until soft.
Peel and chop potatoes into small bite size pieces.
Add to the pepper and onion mixture.
Pour in one can of chicken broth and enough water to just cover the potatoes.
Cook until the potatoes are completely done.
After potatoes are cooked, cut up the cheese and stir in the potatoes.
After cheese is melted, stir in milk until desired thickness.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds and keep in sealed container.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 items in bowl.
Melt shortening.
Add buttermilk over eggs and shortening to cornmeal mix.
Beat well.
Grease pan. Fill half full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Eat with bean soup.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream
sugar
and
shortening.	Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt
and	soda.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.	Add apples and nuts.
Stir into batter.
Pour into a greased loaf pan. Combine
sugar
(3	tablespoons) and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12 baking dish. Drain sweet potatoes well. Mash up with a fork. Beat eggs. Melt butter. Add eggs, vanilla, sugar, milk and butter to sweet potatoes. Mix well. Spread into pan.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, marshmallows and pineapple in bowl. Mix well. Form balls. Roll in coconut. Place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Crumble about a pound of ground beef into a skillet and brown slightly.
Drain meat and transfer into stew pan.
Add water, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook until almost done.
Add onions, green pepper, carrots and potatoes.
(May add 1 cup okra). After vegetables are tender, add 2 cups tomatoes or juice. Simmer 10 minutes and serve with hot cornbread.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Pour margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar a little bit at a time. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternating with milk.
Begin and end with flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube cake pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake on 300° for 45 minutes.
While cake is still hot, cover with marshmallows.

title: cheese soup
directions: Stir gently until melted.
This is delicious and can be frozen.
Makes approximately 5 quarts.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Recipe may be doubled.
Bake two pies and freeze one for later use.

title: muslikkaphrakat(finnish blueberry bars)
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, egg and baking powder in bowl; mix well.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup mixture. Press remaining dough in ball.
Roll on floured surface.
Press over bottom and sides of pan.
Dough will be crumbly.
Press pieces together in pan.

title: country-style barbecued ribs(venison ribs)
directions: If using pork country-style ribs, cook, covered, in boiling water 45 to 60 minutes. Drain.
If using venison ribs, do not precook.

title: hot ham salad sandwich(serves 8)
directions: Combine eggs, ham, celery, pickle, green onions and add enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Cover 8 slices bread with a slice of cheese and top with filling.
Place one slice on top.
Place margarine on top slice and place on oven broiler pan.
Put under broiler at 475° until golden brown.
Turn sandwiches and repeat. Serve with mug of hot tomato soup or cream of broccoli or cream of celery.

title: cheese and egg casserole(for breakfast)
directions: Mix all into beaten eggs.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 325° for
50 to 60 minutes.
Let set for about 10 minutes; then cut into squares and serve.
Serves 8.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in an airtight container.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
Combine potatoes, sugar, margarine, milk, eggs, orange rind and nuts, beating well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Yield: 1 loaf or 18 (1/2-inch) slices.
Contains 122 calories per slice.
Contains protein 2.5, Fat 4.4, Carbohydrate 18.6, Fiber 0.2, Cholesterol 30, Sodium 120, Potassium 82.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and carrots until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer.

title: holiday ham
directions: Cook ham skin side down.
Before cooking, trim off excess fat and lightly score meat in two directions.
Insert 6 to 12 whole cloves to taste.
Heat until well blended the brown sugar, honey and lemon juice.
Spread quickly over ham.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May be served warm or cold.
Keep bone for seasoning for ham bone soup or beans.
Double recice for a whole ham.

title: breaded veal steaks(wiener schnitzel)
directions: Beat steaks until thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip into flour, then in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in shortening until brown on both sides.
Garnish with lemon wedges. Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put blueberries, sugar and cornstarch in heavy saucepan and cook slowly until starts to thicken, stirring constantly.
(Cooks in less than 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and let cool.
Bake pie shells and let cool.
Mix and beat until well mixed the cream cheese, nuts and sugar.
Spread 1/2 of mixture into each pie shell.
Top with half of blueberry mixture on each.
Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well the first 7 ingredients.
Add nuts and apples.
Mix well until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet chicken
directions: In a large skillet, blend soup mix, oil, water, juice and garlic powder.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then bring to boil, stir in chicken, vegetables, spaghetti sauce and wine.
Cook, uncovered 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until the chicken is done. Serve over hot rice.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven, combine onion, green pepper, flour, oil and garlic.
Cook, stirring until vegetables are tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, chili, basil and bay leaf.
Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a 2-quart dish. Place in microwave and bring to a boil, then cook on High 2 minutes.
Remove and add baking soda; stir well.

title: okra muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease muffin pans.
Place empty pans into oven at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove and spoon batter into pans and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper. Lightly grease amini (or regular) muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup, brush oil on each wrapper.
Bake 5 minutes, until golden.
Remove from tins, place on baking sheets.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: apples deluxe
directions: Heat apples, sugar and spices together. Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes. Toss bread cubes in melted margarine until bread has absorbed all of the margarine. Put the apple mixture in a casserole dish and arrange bread cubes on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bread crumbs are crisp. Serves 6.

title: no clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan; crumble.
Set aside.
Add onion rings and cook until lightly browned.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook over medium heat until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until heated through.
Do not boil.
Serve in bowls; top with bacon.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs and set egg whites aside.
Mix together eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Cook on top of stove until boiling starts. Stir constantly!
Add fresh coconut.
If not thick enough, add pinch of flour mix with water.
This will thicken the mixture. (Do not let the pie filling boil because eggs will cook.) Pour filling in pie shells.
Take egg white and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Put on top of pie and brown quickly in oven.

title: a healthy start
directions: Serve at once; enjoy.
It will fill you up for 3 to 4 hours.

title: hawaiian carrots
directions: Mix and cook until it coats spoon.
Pour over fresh cooked carrots (cut up carrots).
Heat and serve.

title: harlequin fish stew
directions: Skin and cut the fish into fairly large pieces, then salt and pepper to taste.
Peel and slice the onion; remove the top and seeds of pepper and cut into thin strips.
Slice the tomatoes thickly; rinse, wipe and slice the mushrooms.
Put the pieces of fish and the prepared vegetables into a deep oven-proof casserole.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Drain all but about 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings from skillet.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and mustard to drippings. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In large bowl, combine drained beans, 1/2 can French fried onions and hot sugar mixture.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon and remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: bigger and better cake mixes
directions: To improve boxed cake mixes, stir the first three ingredients into dry cake mix for a bigger and better cake.
Prepare the cake as directed and add the water, egg and oil in addition.
Bake as directed on the box.

title: harvest bounty
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Spread beans and peppers in dish; sprinkle with tomatoes and cheese.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender until smooth. Pour over vegetables and cheese.
Bake uncovered until golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 12 or more.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Combine preserves, dressing and soup mix in pan over low heat.
Drizzle over chicken pieces.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chewie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: sweet potato pie(better than pumpkin)
directions: Cook potatoes, bake or
boil
until easily pierced with fork. Peel and cool.
Place
in
large
bowl; beat with mixer until smooth.
Add butter and sugar,
beat
in
eggs, one at a time. Mix in salt, nutmeg
and
milk.
Pour into crust.
Beat at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes and cook until tender.
Peel potatoes.
Arrange potatoes in long baking dish. Boil sugar, water, margarine and cinnamon until it starts to thicken.
Add to potatoes and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour (or until syrup is as thick as you want).
Serves 8.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in dishpan in order given.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon perch
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in lemon juice and seasonings. Place fish in skillet, skin side down.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes over medium heat.
Turn; continue cooking until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve butter mixture over fish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tom's chicken or pork chop casserole
directions: Place pats of butter in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle rice all over pan.
Place pork chops or chicken in pan. Spoon soup over chops.
Pour 1 cup water over all.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours for chicken.

title: uncle tom's favorite dessert
directions: Mix cake and bake per directions on pkg., cool. While cake is cooling, mix 2 puddings with 1 1/2 c. milk. Then add 1 qt. ice cream and beat until smooth. Spread over cooled cake and top with Cool Whip.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Add the eggs, milk and vanilla, beat well.
Combine the flour, cocoa, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in the water and mix until smooth.
The batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased and floured 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.
Dust with confectioner's sugar if desired.
Serves 12-16.

title: pineapple carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix sifted flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, mace, salt and sugars.
Add carrots, tossing to coat.
In mixing bowl, combine pineapple, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Pour into original ingredients, stirring to blend. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool at least 10 minutes.

title: slider cake
directions: Make cake mix.
Poke fork holes in cake as soon as you get it out of the oven.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk (whatever pudding calls for) together.
Pour over cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
